1
00:00:18,220 --> 00:00:21,210
Short drama competition show, Director's Arena.

2
00:00:21,210 --> 00:00:24,620
We have 16 directors
who are advancing to Round 2.

3
00:00:24,650 --> 00:00:29,050
Round 2 mission is to co-direct a webtoon.

4
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:30,600
Co-direct?

5
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,380
What?

6
00:00:32,380 --> 00:00:34,660
I think this is the worst.

7
00:00:34,660 --> 00:00:37,290
That's what directors hate the most.
You know, right?

8
00:00:37,290 --> 00:00:41,570
We'll form teams to co-direct webtoons.

9
00:00:41,570 --> 00:00:46,130
The first-place director
of Round 1 will choose first.

10
00:00:46,130 --> 00:00:47,760
How powerful.

11
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:50,420
It's a pair of perfect directors.

12
00:00:50,420 --> 00:00:52,750
They're both too unique.

13
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:54,050
[And]

14
00:00:54,050 --> 00:00:57,650
The people in the broadcasting
industry are so mean.

15
00:00:57,650 --> 00:01:00,320
We won't wait 30 seconds anymore.

16
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:01,620
Huh?

17
00:01:01,620 --> 00:01:04,920
[This round isn't forgiving]

18
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:07,890
I pressed it at the 59-second mark.

19
00:01:07,890 --> 00:01:10,420
Let me be a bit harsh.

20
00:01:10,420 --> 00:01:12,480
It might be boring.

21
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:15,000
I was so embarrassed.

22
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,830
I'm most excited for this team.

23
00:01:16,830 --> 00:01:19,580
The kind of director actors hate the most.

24
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:21,160
We got a lot of stops.

25
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:25,460
Those two won't work together next time.

26
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:27,090
Clashing already?

27
00:01:27,090 --> 00:01:28,150
[What happens to them?]

28
00:01:28,150 --> 00:01:31,240
Short drama competition show, Director's Arena.

29
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:32,690
Round 2 mission.

30
00:01:32,690 --> 00:01:36,910
We gathered 14 webtoons here.

31
00:01:37,390 --> 00:01:41,030
[Make Episode 1 of a webtoon-based short drama!]

32
00:01:41,030 --> 00:01:42,690
These ones, huh?

33
00:01:42,690 --> 00:01:44,090
Hold on.

34
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:46,850
What a dopamine rush.

35
00:01:46,850 --> 00:01:49,990
Director Lee, you adapted "Dakgangjeong*."
(Deep-fried chicken)

36
00:01:49,990 --> 00:01:55,250
Yes, I made a series based on "Dakgangjeong."

37
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:57,720
My webtoon was pretty short.

38
00:01:57,720 --> 00:02:00,520
But in this mission,

39
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:02,860
the content must be much longer
than the running time we've allowed.

40
00:02:02,860 --> 00:02:05,260
It's about condensing it cleverly.

41
00:02:05,260 --> 00:02:07,990
I think that's the battle.

42
00:02:07,990 --> 00:02:12,500
I hope we get good webtoon dramas out of these.

43
00:02:12,550 --> 00:02:18,150
Okay, then. Let's form the
webtoon co-directing teams.

44
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:22,710
Each person can come out
and name a partner of choice.

45
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:25,170
- The first person to choose is...
- Oh, my God.

46
00:02:25,170 --> 00:02:27,260
[In what order will they choose?]

47
00:02:27,260 --> 00:02:30,580
the first-place director of Round 1.

48
00:02:30,580 --> 00:02:32,690
[Lee Yoo Jin will choose his partner first]

49
00:02:32,690 --> 00:02:35,020
Please come forward.

50
00:02:35,020 --> 00:02:37,260
[Jealous]

51
00:02:37,350 --> 00:02:38,740
You're in the Top 3, right?

52
00:02:38,740 --> 00:02:40,820
[The second place starts to worry now]

53
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:42,300
Who should I choose?

54
00:02:43,170 --> 00:02:46,820
[The high-ranking directors have many options]

55
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:49,420
- Director Lee Yoo Jin, are you ready?
- Yes.

56
00:02:49,420 --> 00:02:55,040
Name the director you want to work with.

57
00:02:56,380 --> 00:02:59,650
The person I want to work with is...

58
00:03:00,460 --> 00:03:04,820
[The directors who are waiting
for the moment of choice]

59
00:03:05,350 --> 00:03:07,250
[Who will it be?]

60
00:03:07,260 --> 00:03:11,000
The moment I heard it would be a team mission,

61
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,280
I thought of this person immediately.

62
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:15,910
[Lee Yoo Jin's choice]

63
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:17,780
Director Han Soo Ji.

64
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:21,050
- Director Han Soo Ji.
- Me?

65
00:03:21,050 --> 00:03:22,850
[3rd place, Director Han Soo Ji]

66
00:03:22,850 --> 00:03:26,350
The first-place director chose
the third-place director.

67
00:03:26,350 --> 00:03:28,460
When I saw her teaser...

68
00:03:28,460 --> 00:03:31,230
[Impressed from the beginning]

69
00:03:31,230 --> 00:03:33,960
[Totally absorbed]

70
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:38,120
It was the only one I thought was different.

71
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:40,660
I was like, "Me? Really?"

72
00:03:40,660 --> 00:03:42,630
I was very happy.

73
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:46,660
First and third place.

74
00:03:46,660 --> 00:03:48,470
Powerful.

75
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:49,920
They're the Avengers.

76
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:52,840
It's a pair of perfect directors.

77
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,800
I thought it'd be tough.

78
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:57,810
Director Han Sang Il, please come forward.

79
00:03:57,810 --> 00:03:59,960
[The powerful doghouse scene]

80
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,270
It's short and powerful.

81
00:04:01,270 --> 00:04:02,550
It was amazing.

82
00:04:02,550 --> 00:04:06,930
I laughed out loud at Director Han's teaser.

83
00:04:06,930 --> 00:04:09,150
His lines were so witty, too.

84
00:04:09,150 --> 00:04:11,360
His techniques are masterful, too.

85
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:14,000
I would love to work with him.

86
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,490
Please name a director.

87
00:04:15,490 --> 00:04:18,950
I choose... Was it Director Jang Ju?

88
00:04:18,950 --> 00:04:21,050
[There's no Jang Ju]

89
00:04:21,050 --> 00:04:23,550
Director Jeong Joo?

90
00:04:23,550 --> 00:04:24,980
Director Jeong Joo.

91
00:04:24,980 --> 00:04:26,530
Wow.

92
00:04:26,550 --> 00:04:30,750
It's hard to say based on his expression,

93
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:33,140
- but he was chosen.
- They're both too unique.

94
00:04:33,140 --> 00:04:34,490
I know.

95
00:04:34,490 --> 00:04:37,840
[Jeong Joo's "No Humans"]

96
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,540
[Startled]

97
00:04:40,540 --> 00:04:45,090
[Everyone in the studio was transfixed]

98
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:47,850
It was so engaging.

99
00:04:47,850 --> 00:04:50,980
I'm curious why you picked Director Jeong Joo.

100
00:04:50,980 --> 00:04:55,310
My biggest weaknesses as a director are

101
00:04:55,310 --> 00:04:57,200
mise-en-scène* and visuals.
(Stage arrangement)

102
00:04:57,200 --> 00:05:00,250
I can make him do everything I'm bad at.

103
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:02,690
I thought someone like that would be good.

104
00:05:02,690 --> 00:05:04,110
What do you think, Director?

105
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:06,740
The roles have been determined.

106
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:08,110
Make him do everything?

107
00:05:08,110 --> 00:05:09,750
My problem is now yours.

108
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:15,640
It's like Director Jeong was chosen
as an assistant director.

109
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:18,090
[The directors who weren't chosen yet]

110
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:19,850
[Nervous]

111
00:05:19,850 --> 00:05:23,490
If I can, I'd choose Director Lee Joo Seung.

112
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:26,030
- Lee Joo Seung.
- Actor Lee Joo Seung.

113
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:27,980
Every director must want him.

114
00:05:27,980 --> 00:05:30,830
The network of actors he knows,
who are potential casts.

115
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:34,210
That's a huge asset.

116
00:05:34,210 --> 00:05:37,630
I want to work with Director Lee Joo Seung.

117
00:05:37,630 --> 00:05:41,230
Wow, he chose Director Lee Joo Seung.

118
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:45,270
I was paired with an experienced
short-drama director.

119
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:46,500
It's a relief.

120
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,100
I feel relaxed now.

121
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:53,310
I've directed and produced
over 20 short-form dramas.

122
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:58,160
[Passed Round 1 easily, displaying
textbook short-form drama]

123
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:02,710
[Director Lee Dong Hun's short drama was a hit]

124
00:06:02,710 --> 00:06:04,670
He's on another level.

125
00:06:04,670 --> 00:06:07,530
[The two masters meet]

126
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:10,260
So amazing.

127
00:06:10,260 --> 00:06:12,390
- You can beat him.
- That's true.

128
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:14,830
You can beat him with acting.

129
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:18,790
I choose Director Kwon Sun Yong.

130
00:06:18,790 --> 00:06:21,330
I want to work with you.

131
00:06:21,330 --> 00:06:23,120
Director Yun Hyeong Shik.

132
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:25,390
Director Eun Jong Hun.

133
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:27,350
[The seats were filled before]

134
00:06:27,350 --> 00:06:30,650
[Only two left now...]

135
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,630
[15th place, Oh Hae On]

136
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:35,290
Since we're students,

137
00:06:35,290 --> 00:06:38,150
I knew we wouldn't be chosen.

138
00:06:38,150 --> 00:06:40,120
But as each person left,

139
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:43,220
I felt a bit hurt.

140
00:06:44,780 --> 00:06:46,660
Oh, no...

141
00:06:46,660 --> 00:06:48,000
[Head down]

142
00:06:49,170 --> 00:06:51,880
[Empty]

143
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,580
What do we do?

144
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:55,210
It's like they're being eliminated.

145
00:06:55,210 --> 00:06:56,930
[Hehe]

146
00:06:56,930 --> 00:06:58,500
Talk, at least.

147
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:00,560
You'll become a team.

148
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,130
Gosh...

149
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:06,150
- Team Oh Hae On are kids.
- Right.

150
00:07:06,150 --> 00:07:10,950
They must've been hesitant
to work with kids, I think.

151
00:07:10,970 --> 00:07:13,080
[The last remaining two]

152
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:15,770
I wouldn't have chosen her if I had a choice.

153
00:07:15,770 --> 00:07:19,430
But I had no choice since my rank was low.

154
00:07:19,430 --> 00:07:23,570
I'm worried about how we'd communicate.

155
00:07:23,570 --> 00:07:27,100
We've never worked with adults before.

156
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:31,810
I'm worried we'd drag our partner down.

157
00:07:31,810 --> 00:07:35,920
That's what I'm most worried about now.

158
00:07:36,590 --> 00:07:39,840
[How can they overcome this challenge?]

159
00:07:41,570 --> 00:07:44,570
[Eight teams are formed for Round 2]

160
00:07:44,570 --> 00:07:48,410
We have 14 webtoons to choose from.

161
00:07:48,410 --> 00:07:50,870
You'll be choosing one of them.

162
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:54,580
Each webtoon has a hidden item.

163
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:56,680
What is it? What is it?

164
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,490
What could it be?

165
00:07:59,290 --> 00:08:01,440
[1. Film equipment provided]

166
00:08:01,450 --> 00:08:05,580
Getting film equipment is probably the best.

167
00:08:05,580 --> 00:08:08,700
I liked it. Film equipment tends to be pricey.

168
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:11,210
But we get to rent everything.

169
00:08:11,210 --> 00:08:14,090
[2. Work with a world-class
music producer, Raiden]

170
00:08:14,090 --> 00:08:16,500
[3. Deadline delayed by a day]

171
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:19,310
[And two secret actor cards]

172
00:08:19,670 --> 00:08:22,500
[Which teams will win hidden items?]

173
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:25,510
Please choose the webtoons now.

174
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:27,550
I think...

175
00:08:27,990 --> 00:08:30,530
[She prefers the romance genre]

176
00:08:30,530 --> 00:08:34,010
I can do comedy and serious stuff.

177
00:08:34,010 --> 00:08:35,050
Okay.

178
00:08:35,050 --> 00:08:38,420
[Choosing the webtoon that can
create synergy is the goal]

179
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:41,850
[Letting the older person choose first]

180
00:08:41,850 --> 00:08:44,600
I think that one would be good.

181
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,900
[Suggesting the one he wants]

182
00:08:47,350 --> 00:08:50,190
[Not an easy decision to make]

183
00:08:50,470 --> 00:08:53,600
[Will the co-directing go smoothly?]

184
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,630
I'm confident.

185
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:58,160
- First place.
- We have to survive somehow.

186
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,840
[They're only given two weeks]

187
00:09:03,450 --> 00:09:05,920
The background looks a bit dark.

188
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,010
[Can't miss even one scene!]

189
00:09:07,010 --> 00:09:08,460
That will be the subtext.

190
00:09:08,460 --> 00:09:10,010
I can't keep up.

191
00:09:10,010 --> 00:09:13,150
[Unlimited passion]

192
00:09:14,110 --> 00:09:16,960
[Betting on their 120-second dash]

193
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:19,910
[The exciting short dramas
will be revealed soon!]

194
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:29,560
[Round 2]

195
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,720
[The day of the battle]

196
00:09:32,350 --> 00:09:36,650
[All Round 2 contestants have entered]

197
00:09:37,140 --> 00:09:39,370
[The judging panel is back again today]

198
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:41,800
[The viewers have entered]

199
00:09:44,540 --> 00:09:47,050
[All the seats are filled]

200
00:09:47,050 --> 00:09:49,050
I'm so curious.

201
00:09:49,050 --> 00:09:51,250
I can't wait to see the other people's work.

202
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:53,730
Everyone must have done a good job this time.

203
00:09:53,730 --> 00:09:55,790
You think? I guess so.

204
00:09:55,790 --> 00:10:00,150
They know everyone else's abilities by now.

205
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:01,580
I'm excited.

206
00:10:01,580 --> 00:10:03,370
It's like a film preview.

207
00:10:03,370 --> 00:10:05,590
Ours isn't bad.

208
00:10:05,590 --> 00:10:07,870
I have no regrets... Whatever. Dang it.

209
00:10:07,870 --> 00:10:09,830
- Ours isn't bad.
- I'm scared.

210
00:10:09,830 --> 00:10:12,630
- I suddenly want to puke.
- You want to puke?

211
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:14,700
You're so shocked.

212
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:16,840
I'll find you a plastic bag.

213
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:19,060
[Another nervous person]

214
00:10:19,060 --> 00:10:21,350
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

215
00:10:21,350 --> 00:10:24,350
- Are you nervous?
- Yes, a little bit.

216
00:10:24,350 --> 00:10:28,130
[When you're nervous, you eat!]

217
00:10:28,130 --> 00:10:30,630
You guys love that stuff.

218
00:10:31,650 --> 00:10:36,340
[Get the popcorn ready. It's snack time.]

219
00:10:37,660 --> 00:10:39,950
[The viewers are enjoying them, too]

220
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:45,010
[Getting small comforts while feeling nervous]

221
00:10:45,950 --> 00:10:48,650
[He's having a full-on meal]

222
00:10:49,350 --> 00:10:51,410
[Can't stop eating]

223
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:54,890
[Their mood has been lifted]

224
00:10:54,890 --> 00:10:57,590
[Saving it for the fun short dramas later]

225
00:10:57,590 --> 00:10:59,830
They got an air purifier sponsorship.

226
00:11:00,370 --> 00:11:02,600
[In charge of the Director's Arena's fresh air]

227
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:05,340
You're right. There's an air purifier.

228
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:07,730
[The air of capitalism]

229
00:11:07,730 --> 00:11:10,580
I noticed how clean the air was.

230
00:11:10,580 --> 00:11:12,130
I can feel the air coming.

231
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:14,850
Yes, the air is fresher than last time.

232
00:11:14,990 --> 00:11:18,860
[Round 2 got more pleasant]

233
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:19,770
Hello.

234
00:11:19,770 --> 00:11:22,020
[Finally starting]

235
00:11:22,020 --> 00:11:24,700
[Good to see you]

236
00:11:24,700 --> 00:11:27,400
The unstoppable K-dopamine battle.

237
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:32,360
Korea's first short drama competition
show, Director's Arena.

238
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:35,680
Hello, I'll guide you into the
world of short dramas.

239
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:38,730
I'm the short drama guide, Jang Do Yeon.

240
00:11:39,620 --> 00:11:42,150
Good to see you. Good to see you.

241
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:43,950
Stop if it's not entertaining.

242
00:11:43,950 --> 00:11:47,050
Round 1's 90-second mission was a battle.

243
00:11:47,050 --> 00:11:52,500
33 directors joined the competition,
and only 16 survived.

244
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:57,230
Let me introduce you to the
16 directors who are in Round 2.

245
00:11:57,230 --> 00:11:58,860
Welcome.

246
00:11:58,860 --> 00:12:02,930
[The 16 people who survived a fierce competition]

247
00:12:02,930 --> 00:12:05,020
You must've worked so hard.

248
00:12:05,020 --> 00:12:07,850
They're here to judge harshly again today.

249
00:12:07,850 --> 00:12:10,210
Thirty-two viewers, welcome to the show.

250
00:12:10,210 --> 00:12:11,660
[32 viewers]

251
00:12:11,660 --> 00:12:12,910
Nice to meet you.

252
00:12:12,910 --> 00:12:15,370
Lastly, the Five Stars are here.

253
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:17,070
[Cha Tae Hyun]

254
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:19,290
[Jang Keun Suk]

255
00:12:19,290 --> 00:12:21,370
[Lee Byeong Heon]

256
00:12:21,370 --> 00:12:25,260
Let's start Director's Arena Round 2.

257
00:12:25,260 --> 00:12:28,350
[What kind of short dramas
will we see in Round 2?]

258
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,710
I'm very excited.

259
00:12:30,710 --> 00:12:33,820
I think we'll see higher-quality creations.

260
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:36,210
I'm more confident than I was in Round 1.

261
00:12:36,250 --> 00:12:40,150
It's all about talent, not resumes,
on Director's Arena.

262
00:12:40,150 --> 00:12:44,800
Round 2 mission is co-directing a webtoon.

263
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:50,670
I'm excited to see how you turned
webtoons into short dramas.

264
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:55,350
Director Lee, how does this differ
from Round 1's teaser mission?

265
00:12:55,350 --> 00:12:57,500
That was a teaser, and this is an episode.

266
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,760
- Teasers are...
- Oh, I see.

267
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:01,740
- I thought I heard him wrong.
- I see.

268
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:07,220
But in short dramas, the first
episode is like a teaser, too.

269
00:13:07,220 --> 00:13:11,650
You have to present your identity
quickly and effectively.

270
00:13:11,650 --> 00:13:14,830
I think in short drama, the first
episode is also a teaser.

271
00:13:14,830 --> 00:13:17,040
- But more impactful.
- You have to constantly show off.

272
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:19,890
- This is harder.
- I know.

273
00:13:19,890 --> 00:13:23,050
Let me tell you how Round 2's judging works.

274
00:13:23,050 --> 00:13:26,150
While watching, if you no longer
want to watch it,

275
00:13:26,150 --> 00:13:28,400
press the stop button.

276
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:32,350
The ranking will be determined
by the average viewing time.

277
00:13:32,350 --> 00:13:36,240
So far, it's the same as the last time.

278
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,140
Something must be different.

279
00:13:38,140 --> 00:13:41,350
But this time, cruelly,

280
00:13:41,350 --> 00:13:44,310
we won't wait 30 seconds.

281
00:13:44,310 --> 00:13:45,560
Huh?

282
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:49,430
[You were able to vote
after 30 seconds in Round 1]

283
00:13:49,430 --> 00:13:51,340
[Vote]

284
00:13:51,350 --> 00:13:53,440
[Stop count]

285
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:56,520
[You can stop as soon as the video starts]

286
00:13:58,350 --> 00:14:00,220
[All they can do is laugh]

287
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:02,720
- Oh, my God.
- That's rough.

288
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:06,320
The people in the broadcasting
industry are so mean.

289
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:08,830
They thought about how to humiliate us.

290
00:14:08,830 --> 00:14:11,570
You're not given time to get into it this time.

291
00:14:11,570 --> 00:14:14,270
So, I think I was more afraid.

292
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:17,740
Out of the eight teams competing in Round 2,

293
00:14:17,740 --> 00:14:20,570
three teams will be eliminated.

294
00:14:20,570 --> 00:14:22,620
[Deep sigh]

295
00:14:22,970 --> 00:14:24,420
[Getting more nervous]

296
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:26,220
[Whining]

297
00:14:26,220 --> 00:14:27,930
There will be just the Top 10 left.

298
00:14:27,930 --> 00:14:29,750
It's not too bad, right?

299
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:33,080
We'll at least be somewhere in the middle.

300
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:36,650
I'd like to ask Director Han Sang Il a question.

301
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:39,800
I was told that Director Han Sang Il

302
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:44,830
came up with a unique winning strategy.

303
00:14:44,830 --> 00:14:47,050
It's not exactly a winning strategy.

304
00:14:47,050 --> 00:14:51,940
It's important for us to do well and succeed,

305
00:14:51,950 --> 00:14:56,950
but how much they screwed up
is much more crucial.

306
00:14:56,970 --> 00:14:59,040
Because it's all relative?

307
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:01,590
- You're right.
- That's your strategy?

308
00:15:01,590 --> 00:15:03,830
If I get eliminated in Round 2...

309
00:15:03,850 --> 00:15:06,350
I told the producer this, too, but...

310
00:15:06,350 --> 00:15:08,960
I'll set this building on fire.

311
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:13,720
Have you been upset about a lot of things?

312
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:15,410
Your tone is a bit...

313
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:16,980
[Just have to laugh]

314
00:15:17,050 --> 00:15:20,350
- I'm known for complaining a lot.
- A complainer.

315
00:15:20,370 --> 00:15:21,720
[He'll be freer]

316
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:24,320
We can't avoid interviewing this director.

317
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:27,770
It's our first-place director,
Director Lee Yoo Jin.

318
00:15:27,770 --> 00:15:30,790
Have you come up with the winning strategy?

319
00:15:30,790 --> 00:15:32,290
Winning strategy?

320
00:15:32,290 --> 00:15:37,600
The people who got good scores in the beginning

321
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,580
tend to do worse as the underdogs

322
00:15:39,580 --> 00:15:42,580
- start moving on up.
- The trajectory of competition shows.

323
00:15:42,580 --> 00:15:44,220
It usually is.

324
00:15:44,220 --> 00:15:45,970
Will you crash right away, then?

325
00:15:45,970 --> 00:15:47,430
Come on.

326
00:15:47,430 --> 00:15:49,280
You can't say that to their faces.

327
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:52,710
But this show won't be on the same trajectory.

328
00:15:52,710 --> 00:15:53,710
Wow.

329
00:15:53,710 --> 00:15:56,020
[So confident]

330
00:15:56,020 --> 00:15:58,920
They'll move on up steadily.

331
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:02,170
Let's start Round 2 immediately.

332
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:05,870
Round 2 mission, co-direct a webtoon.

333
00:16:05,870 --> 00:16:07,950
Let's start judging.

334
00:16:07,950 --> 00:16:09,420
[It's short drama time!]

335
00:16:09,420 --> 00:16:12,080
[Three teams will be eliminated in Round 2]

336
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:13,680
[So nervous]

337
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:16,700
Let's meet the first team, then.

338
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:19,030
Who will go first?

339
00:16:19,030 --> 00:16:21,960
- It just can't be us.
- Going first isn't bad.

340
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:24,550
I think going first gives you a disadvantage.

341
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:27,670
We just need to avoid going first.

342
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:31,960
[Which team will be named first?]

343
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:38,130
The director who dreamt of being on TV...

344
00:16:38,130 --> 00:16:39,540
That must be us.

345
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:41,030
And the director who's always on TV...

346
00:16:41,030 --> 00:16:42,990
Are you looking forward to being on TV?

347
00:16:42,990 --> 00:16:45,300
I never dreamt of being an actor,

348
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:48,190
but I've always wanted to be on TV.

349
00:16:48,190 --> 00:16:51,450
And the director who's always on TV united.

350
00:16:51,450 --> 00:16:55,450
The Lee brothers' "Meet My Roommate."

351
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:57,180
Please come forward.

352
00:16:57,180 --> 00:17:00,520
I was a bit nervous about them.

353
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:02,460
It's an interesting combination of directors.

354
00:17:02,460 --> 00:17:05,510
I thought they'd create something fun.

355
00:17:05,510 --> 00:17:08,250
[Lee Dong Hun and Lee Joo Seung go first]

356
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:12,610
"Meet My Roommate" is about a man
and a woman with the same name

357
00:17:12,610 --> 00:17:17,300
being assigned to the same dorm
due to a system error.

358
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:20,030
Wow, so cool!

359
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:23,360
Joo Seung acted in it.

360
00:17:24,130 --> 00:17:26,390
We're Korea's-

361
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:29,180
[Already funny]

362
00:17:29,180 --> 00:17:31,640
Huh? Clashing already?

363
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:35,290
- We're Korea's...
- Wachowski brothers.

364
00:17:35,350 --> 00:17:37,170
[Still not in sync]

365
00:17:37,390 --> 00:17:39,910
[Comedians, not directors?]

366
00:17:39,910 --> 00:17:43,880
It looked like you weren't totally in sync,

367
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:46,900
but I heard you were very much on the same page.

368
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:50,350
That's right. While preparing for the mission,

369
00:17:50,350 --> 00:17:54,340
we went to a cafe in Hapjeong
and had multiple dates.

370
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:56,070
You went on dates?

371
00:17:56,070 --> 00:17:58,990
He bought me a steak, too.

372
00:17:59,770 --> 00:18:02,200
We created a lot of fond memories.

373
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:04,460
You keep going on about your dates.

374
00:18:04,460 --> 00:18:06,230
What? Fond memories?

375
00:18:06,230 --> 00:18:08,110
They must've had fun.

376
00:18:08,110 --> 00:18:09,950
Bromance.

377
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:13,890
We've talked about this a lot,

378
00:18:13,890 --> 00:18:17,160
but we tried to become a good team.

379
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:18,780
I bought him a steak.

380
00:18:18,780 --> 00:18:21,740
We talked a lot while cutting the steaks.

381
00:18:21,740 --> 00:18:25,830
We went to cafes where couples go,

382
00:18:25,850 --> 00:18:28,950
got coffee, and sunbathed, too.

383
00:18:28,950 --> 00:18:32,200
I thought he was blunt at first,

384
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:35,550
but I realized he was caring
as we worked together.

385
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:37,550
It was fun.

386
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:41,330
Director Lee Dong Hun, as a working
short drama director,

387
00:18:41,330 --> 00:18:45,470
how did you like the male lead?

388
00:18:45,470 --> 00:18:47,690
He was very passionate.

389
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:51,170
Especially... You'll be seeing it later,

390
00:18:51,170 --> 00:18:53,760
but he insisted on wearing nothing but underwear.

391
00:18:53,760 --> 00:18:56,630
He's not afraid to go the extra mile...

392
00:18:56,630 --> 00:18:58,150
You omitted the context.

393
00:18:58,150 --> 00:19:00,420
He insisted on only wearing underwear.

394
00:19:00,420 --> 00:19:01,920
[Insisted on wearing nothing but underwear]

395
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:04,990
Nothing but underwear?

396
00:19:04,990 --> 00:19:08,860
He was willing to sacrifice
his body for the scenes.

397
00:19:08,860 --> 00:19:10,230
That's what I thought.

398
00:19:10,230 --> 00:19:12,550
And he's very good at writing dialogues.

399
00:19:12,550 --> 00:19:16,270
I showed him the script, and we discussed.

400
00:19:16,270 --> 00:19:18,400
But I guess he didn't like my script.

401
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:20,080
He kept turning it down at first.

402
00:19:20,080 --> 00:19:22,060
He later wrote the script himself.

403
00:19:22,060 --> 00:19:25,320
I was captured by some of the lines, too.

404
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:26,580
He's very good with comedy.

405
00:19:26,580 --> 00:19:28,260
They must've had a good time.

406
00:19:29,190 --> 00:19:31,660
[How did they enjoy their time together?]

407
00:19:32,670 --> 00:19:36,070
[On a cherry-blossom-filled April day]

408
00:19:36,070 --> 00:19:37,480
The first scene will be shot from there.

409
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,450
[Lee Dong Hun and Lee Joo Seung's set]

410
00:19:39,450 --> 00:19:43,350
I've shot a short drama before in this space.

411
00:19:43,410 --> 00:19:46,020
I know the owner well.

412
00:19:46,020 --> 00:19:48,280
We were able to rent it on good terms.

413
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:51,180
[Rented a sophisticated space]

414
00:19:51,870 --> 00:19:53,580
Hello.

415
00:19:53,580 --> 00:19:55,600
Oh, hello. Hello.

416
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:57,160
Hello.

417
00:19:57,160 --> 00:19:58,570
Your hair...

418
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:00,950
Are you acting in it?

419
00:20:00,950 --> 00:20:03,940
- They kept filming me.
- Did you use hair mousse?

420
00:20:03,940 --> 00:20:06,760
I put it on for once. I'm on it, too.

421
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:08,460
You're serious.

422
00:20:08,460 --> 00:20:11,110
He's very happy about being on TV.

423
00:20:11,150 --> 00:20:14,210
It's always been your dream.

424
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:16,510
I'll teach you how to act. You're acting today.

425
00:20:16,510 --> 00:20:20,380
We'll swap. I'll make your dream come true.

426
00:20:20,890 --> 00:20:22,370
You haven't changed your pants.

427
00:20:22,370 --> 00:20:24,190
They're underwear, actually.

428
00:20:24,190 --> 00:20:27,120
I wasn't sure when to change.

429
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:30,910
I think I've never acted in trunks before.

430
00:20:30,910 --> 00:20:34,200
I'll try wearing a mini skirt next time.

431
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,880
[Satisfied with the costume]

432
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:37,990
[Lee Dong Hun's job: Unpacking props]

433
00:20:37,990 --> 00:20:39,450
Did you choose the costumes yourself?

434
00:20:39,450 --> 00:20:43,080
Yes, Joo Seung and I picked them out.

435
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:46,460
He's very detail-oriented.

436
00:20:46,460 --> 00:20:50,970
He requested very specific items.

437
00:20:50,970 --> 00:20:52,770
It was hard to pick them,

438
00:20:52,770 --> 00:20:56,610
but I'm excited because they will look nice.

439
00:20:56,610 --> 00:20:58,980
How did the table read go yesterday?

440
00:20:58,980 --> 00:21:02,890
The table read was like a thriller movie.

441
00:21:02,890 --> 00:21:05,860
They're strict about the two-minute length.

442
00:21:05,860 --> 00:21:09,720
[Director Lee Dong Hun's first table read]

443
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:12,430
I'll start the timer as we start.

444
00:21:12,430 --> 00:21:14,120
Okay.

445
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:16,600
Start.

446
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:19,520
Okay, got it.

447
00:21:19,550 --> 00:21:20,950
[First time around]

448
00:21:20,950 --> 00:21:22,530
What did they say?

449
00:21:22,530 --> 00:21:24,120
We used a timer.

450
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:27,990
We recorded time as if we were
clocking Olympic records.

451
00:21:27,990 --> 00:21:29,570
How many minutes was that?

452
00:21:29,570 --> 00:21:32,190
We got 2 minutes and 54 seconds.

453
00:21:33,590 --> 00:21:35,290
Let's remove this, too.

454
00:21:35,290 --> 00:21:38,000
I wonder if we can shorten this.

455
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:41,260
[The lines keep getting removed]

456
00:21:41,260 --> 00:21:43,870
[My script...]

457
00:21:43,950 --> 00:21:47,750
Assistant Director, I need you
to ask the question very quickly.

458
00:21:47,780 --> 00:21:49,430
You can't laugh.

459
00:21:49,430 --> 00:21:51,750
There's no time. We have
to finish in two minutes.

460
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:53,640
There's no time to laugh.

461
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,610
[Lee Joo Seung's 2-minute training]

462
00:21:55,610 --> 00:21:57,370
[What is the outcome?]

463
00:21:59,450 --> 00:22:02,350
One minute and 53 seconds. We did it.

464
00:22:03,260 --> 00:22:05,960
We started saving time as we practiced.

465
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:08,730
I'm relieved. I would've been
nervous if we didn't read.

466
00:22:08,750 --> 00:22:13,550
It was nice that we read together
and met the time limit.

467
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:17,360
[Starting to shoot]

468
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:20,600
[Director Lee Dong Hun/Actor Lee Joo Seung]

469
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,660
[How did you two delegate roles?]

470
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:29,650
On the set, Joo Seung acted, and I monitored.

471
00:22:29,650 --> 00:22:33,020
I realized we were very different.

472
00:22:33,020 --> 00:22:34,490
How many takes?

473
00:22:35,780 --> 00:22:38,880
We understood what created synergy.

474
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:40,940
She's looking up very high.

475
00:22:40,940 --> 00:22:42,690
We should fix that first.

476
00:22:42,690 --> 00:22:45,190
I feel like the shot doesn't look great.

477
00:22:45,190 --> 00:22:46,860
Let me show you first.

478
00:22:46,860 --> 00:22:48,560
[Demonstrating himself]

479
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:50,680
You're lying down like this.

480
00:22:51,550 --> 00:22:55,650
It falls, but it's too far and out of reach.

481
00:22:55,670 --> 00:22:57,190
And then...

482
00:22:57,190 --> 00:22:59,300
[Suddenly doing bromance acting]

483
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:02,740
You should land on him like this.

484
00:23:02,740 --> 00:23:05,380
[Shy]

485
00:23:05,890 --> 00:23:09,650
[What's Lee Joo Seung's role?]

486
00:23:10,050 --> 00:23:12,050
You're just about to speak.

487
00:23:12,050 --> 00:23:15,120
Open your eyes like this.

488
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:17,050
[Like this]

489
00:23:17,050 --> 00:23:19,730
- Like this.
- Okay.

490
00:23:19,750 --> 00:23:23,030
Put your hand over here like this.

491
00:23:23,030 --> 00:23:26,020
[Adjusting the details as a director]

492
00:23:26,020 --> 00:23:28,060
It was as if he sketched, and I added colors.

493
00:23:28,060 --> 00:23:31,060
We communicated very well like that.

494
00:23:31,060 --> 00:23:34,500
It was like creating a painting together.

495
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:36,180
[The two directors' synergy]

496
00:23:36,180 --> 00:23:37,880
[And]

497
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:39,780
Hello.

498
00:23:39,780 --> 00:23:45,920
[A special guest joined the set]

499
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:48,790
Let's see if there's a hidden item for this.

500
00:23:48,790 --> 00:23:50,410
Please reveal.

501
00:23:51,180 --> 00:23:53,940
[iKON's Song Yunhyeong]

502
00:23:53,940 --> 00:23:56,330
[Hidden actor Song Yunhyeong
for "Meet My Roommate"]

503
00:23:56,330 --> 00:23:58,730
[He's taking a shot at short drama acting]

504
00:23:58,730 --> 00:24:00,840
[iKON's best looking member, Song Yunhyeong]

505
00:24:01,350 --> 00:24:03,050
[What's he like as an actor?]

506
00:24:03,990 --> 00:24:05,400
[Acting with a prop]

507
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:08,490
Struggle as if they're heavy like this

508
00:24:08,490 --> 00:24:10,380
and drop all of them like this.

509
00:24:10,380 --> 00:24:12,920
Okay, I'll give it a try.

510
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:17,310
I'm here to try something new on my own.

511
00:24:17,310 --> 00:24:19,720
I just don't want to inconvenience them.

512
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:22,870
I'll just do as I practiced.

513
00:24:22,870 --> 00:24:25,560
[From a singer, turning on his acting mode]

514
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:27,890
Team Leader?

515
00:24:27,890 --> 00:24:32,050
[What kind of short drama did they create?]

516
00:24:32,050 --> 00:24:34,850
We'll start judging now.

517
00:24:34,850 --> 00:24:36,770
The video will play.

518
00:24:36,770 --> 00:24:40,250
You can start voting as soon as the video starts.

519
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:44,450
Now, let's get started.

520
00:24:44,450 --> 00:24:46,330
Play the video.

521
00:24:47,190 --> 00:24:49,460
I'm very confident.

522
00:24:49,460 --> 00:24:52,280
I'm aiming for five stops.

523
00:24:52,280 --> 00:24:54,000
I don't know what people are thinking.

524
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:56,080
"Should I just press stop in the beginning?"

525
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:59,200
They could think that. So, I felt nervous.

526
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:04,930
[Can they capture the 50 viewers' hearts?]

527
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:08,730
[Meet My Roommate]

528
00:25:15,150 --> 00:25:17,430
[Focused, interested]

529
00:25:17,430 --> 00:25:18,660
[Nervous]

530
00:25:18,660 --> 00:25:22,050
[Lee Dong Hun and Lee Joo Seung's
"Meet My Roommate"]

531
00:25:37,060 --> 00:25:41,190
[Meet My Roommate]

532
00:25:41,190 --> 00:25:43,500
[A week ago]

533
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:44,890
First time living alone.

534
00:25:44,890 --> 00:25:47,470
I'm so happy.

535
00:25:51,170 --> 00:25:53,770
- What?
- Team Leader?

536
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:57,300
I'm so happy.

537
00:25:57,300 --> 00:26:00,960
[Got one vote in 28 seconds]

538
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:02,920
[Glancing]

539
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:05,950
The scene with him in his underwear

540
00:26:05,950 --> 00:26:07,920
was supposed to be funny.

541
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:09,380
I thought people would like it.

542
00:26:09,380 --> 00:26:11,330
But they didn't really laugh.

543
00:26:11,330 --> 00:26:13,530
The underwear...

544
00:26:13,530 --> 00:26:17,450
I wondered if he should've
taken his top off, too.

545
00:26:21,550 --> 00:26:24,300
- What?
- Team Leader?

546
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:27,760
Got it.

547
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:28,750
What did they say?

548
00:26:28,750 --> 00:26:32,540
They can't figure it out with the system
because we have the same name.

549
00:26:32,540 --> 00:26:33,930
They want us to figure it out ourselves.

550
00:26:33,930 --> 00:26:35,810
I live in Daejeon.

551
00:26:35,810 --> 00:26:38,510
I gave my room to my brother,
who returned from the army.

552
00:26:38,510 --> 00:26:42,300
So, could you move out instead?

553
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:45,030
- I live in Jeju-do.
- You're lying.

554
00:26:45,960 --> 00:26:48,510
[Getting some reactions]

555
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:50,780
[Nervous]

556
00:26:50,780 --> 00:26:52,440
[The stop count is frozen for a while]

557
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:55,120
- Daejeon is kind of far.
- Right?

558
00:26:55,120 --> 00:26:57,720
- I knew you'd...
- But I have a situation, too.

559
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:59,850
I can never move out. Never.

560
00:27:00,550 --> 00:27:03,160
I can't move out, either. Never.

561
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:04,850
Give up because I'm your superior.

562
00:27:04,850 --> 00:27:09,130
You should give up because I'm your subordinate.

563
00:27:09,130 --> 00:27:11,710
You should give up because...

564
00:27:11,710 --> 00:27:13,780
[Suddenly rising]

565
00:27:13,780 --> 00:27:16,140
[Why do you keep pressing it?]

566
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:17,850
[Mouth drying]

567
00:27:17,850 --> 00:27:20,290
I saw the number changing from the side.

568
00:27:20,290 --> 00:27:23,630
My heart sank whenever I heard the beeps.

569
00:27:24,470 --> 00:27:25,830
Okay.

570
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:29,670
How about we do this?

571
00:27:30,860 --> 00:27:32,560
Here we go.

572
00:27:44,860 --> 00:27:46,370
Heads.

573
00:27:49,210 --> 00:27:51,160
Yay! Wow.

574
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:53,070
Wow. Move out now.

575
00:27:53,070 --> 00:27:55,090
Do it again. Just once more.

576
00:27:55,090 --> 00:27:56,880
- What are you saying?
- Just once more.

577
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:59,520
What are you doing? Get out of my house. Get out.

578
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:01,050
[Laughing]

579
00:28:01,050 --> 00:28:03,000
[Hehehe]

580
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:05,090
Get out of my house. Hurry.

581
00:28:05,090 --> 00:28:08,100
How about we just live together?

582
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:09,440
Pardon?

583
00:28:10,470 --> 00:28:13,060
- Team Leader?
- Il Wu.

584
00:28:14,810 --> 00:28:17,470
[You can watch the full version on Lehzin Snack]

585
00:28:17,470 --> 00:28:20,230
Wow, that went fast.

586
00:28:20,230 --> 00:28:22,700
[The two minutes were like two hours to them]

587
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:25,100
They did a good job.

588
00:28:25,100 --> 00:28:26,700
It's like a real short drama.

589
00:28:26,700 --> 00:28:29,520
Two minutes. Pretty neat.

590
00:28:29,520 --> 00:28:34,800
Directors Lee Dong Hun and
Lee Joo Seung's video ended.

591
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:37,670
You got 14 stops in total.

592
00:28:37,670 --> 00:28:40,190
What do you think? Are you
satisfied with the result?

593
00:28:40,190 --> 00:28:42,160
I'm satisfied, but...

594
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:44,550
I'm curious how the 14 people felt.

595
00:28:44,550 --> 00:28:46,210
[He doesn't seem satisfied]

596
00:28:46,210 --> 00:28:47,550
You must be disappointed.

597
00:28:47,550 --> 00:28:49,600
I'm very disappointed. Fourteen people.

598
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:52,410
How many stops did you expect?

599
00:28:52,410 --> 00:28:56,280
I expected more like two.

600
00:28:56,280 --> 00:28:58,530
You got 12 more.

601
00:28:58,530 --> 00:29:00,010
[Disappointed]

602
00:29:00,010 --> 00:29:01,620
To be honest, I was a bit upset.

603
00:29:01,620 --> 00:29:05,350
I got fewer votes in the first mission.

604
00:29:05,350 --> 00:29:09,030
I realized I might end up falling behind.

605
00:29:09,030 --> 00:29:10,890
I started to have that worry.

606
00:29:10,890 --> 00:29:13,570
But this is the first one we watched.

607
00:29:13,570 --> 00:29:16,790
We can't tell if the number is high or low.

608
00:29:16,790 --> 00:29:20,000
Since we're talking,
what did you think, Tae Hyun?

609
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:22,750
I pressed it at the 59-second mark.

610
00:29:22,750 --> 00:29:25,060
I pressed it at the 59-second mark.

611
00:29:25,060 --> 00:29:27,030
At the 1:59 mark.

612
00:29:27,810 --> 00:29:30,920
[Toward the end]

613
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:32,730
[Glancing]

614
00:29:32,730 --> 00:29:34,770
[Push]

615
00:29:36,630 --> 00:29:39,300
[He pressed exactly at 1:59]

616
00:29:39,300 --> 00:29:42,020
I wanted to check if this works.

617
00:29:42,020 --> 00:29:44,890
Stop lying. You're so sneaky.

618
00:29:44,950 --> 00:29:48,350
The reason is that I wasn't
curious to see Episode 2.

619
00:29:48,350 --> 00:29:51,470
I was hoping for something more provocative.

620
00:29:51,470 --> 00:29:55,460
I think it was lacking that way, personally.

621
00:29:55,460 --> 00:29:57,340
We saw too many intense ones in Round 1.

622
00:29:57,340 --> 00:29:59,550
- You've gotten used to it.
- I'm in trouble.

623
00:29:59,550 --> 00:30:01,370
I'm not so affected by it anymore.

624
00:30:01,370 --> 00:30:03,220
- Your dopamine level already...
- Am I addicted?

625
00:30:03,220 --> 00:30:05,270
That's how it starts.

626
00:30:05,270 --> 00:30:07,190
What do I do?

627
00:30:07,190 --> 00:30:10,130
I'm curious if you changed

628
00:30:10,130 --> 00:30:13,280
the original lines or the plot.

629
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:16,640
Or did you keep the original?

630
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:20,560
We used the original a lot,

631
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:23,550
but we had to tell the story in two minutes.

632
00:30:23,550 --> 00:30:27,250
We used what happens later on
and edited it like that.

633
00:30:27,270 --> 00:30:30,930
I think that got me thinking

634
00:30:30,930 --> 00:30:33,450
that the dialogue wasn't so realistic.

635
00:30:33,450 --> 00:30:38,360
When you explained that having the
same name caused a mix-up,

636
00:30:38,360 --> 00:30:41,730
you could've shown a flashback
of a civil servant or the landlord

637
00:30:41,730 --> 00:30:46,880
mixing things up briefly. It would've been fun.

638
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:51,150
But it was all done in one space.

639
00:30:51,150 --> 00:30:55,140
I wish it had been explained a bit more.

640
00:30:55,140 --> 00:30:56,840
So unforgiving.

641
00:30:57,500 --> 00:30:59,330
So unforgiving.

642
00:31:00,040 --> 00:31:03,370
He's been very critical all along.

643
00:31:03,370 --> 00:31:05,510
- I'm an addict!
- Okay.

644
00:31:05,510 --> 00:31:08,140
It'd be hard to win Keun Suk over.

645
00:31:08,140 --> 00:31:10,010
Right. He's the toughest.

646
00:31:10,010 --> 00:31:14,270
I agree with Keun Suk. I do, but...

647
00:31:14,270 --> 00:31:17,060
I think short dramas have a bit more freedom.

648
00:31:17,060 --> 00:31:19,600
I think you used that well.

649
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:23,780
You can't escape the classic love-hate genre.

650
00:31:23,780 --> 00:31:26,130
It's better to keep it classic in this case.

651
00:31:26,130 --> 00:31:29,980
You did a great job.
It was like a textbook example.

652
00:31:29,980 --> 00:31:31,440
I liked the details from the beginning.

653
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:34,170
The editing and music, too.

654
00:31:34,170 --> 00:31:35,800
And the actors are so engaging.

655
00:31:35,800 --> 00:31:37,630
I wanted to see the next episode.

656
00:31:37,630 --> 00:31:40,870
- Wow.
- I enjoyed it very much.

657
00:31:40,870 --> 00:31:44,920
Let's have a short interview with a viewer.

658
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:48,400
Did you push the stop button by chance?

659
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:51,410
I didn't push it. I enjoyed it
for the entire two minutes.

660
00:31:51,410 --> 00:31:52,850
Why did you like it?

661
00:31:52,850 --> 00:31:59,100
I noticed that Director Lee Joo Seung
was good with dialogue.

662
00:31:59,100 --> 00:32:02,040
"You move out because I'm your superior."

663
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:04,070
That hit me once.

664
00:32:04,070 --> 00:32:05,790
Give up because I'm your superior.

665
00:32:05,790 --> 00:32:09,090
You should give up because
I'm your subordinate.

666
00:32:09,090 --> 00:32:12,790
I was hooked from that point.

667
00:32:12,790 --> 00:32:16,940
The hidden card, Song Yunhyeong,

668
00:32:16,940 --> 00:32:21,280
made a surprise appearance,
and it ended right there.

669
00:32:21,280 --> 00:32:23,330
It ended short and sweet with a bang.

670
00:32:23,350 --> 00:32:26,650
I'd be like, "Whoa," and play the next episode.

671
00:32:26,700 --> 00:32:29,590
- Your strategy worked perfectly.
- I love that.

672
00:32:29,590 --> 00:32:30,830
So well-received.

673
00:32:30,850 --> 00:32:31,870
[You want the mic?]

674
00:32:31,870 --> 00:32:33,650
He wants a handshake.

675
00:32:33,650 --> 00:32:35,150
You aren't syncing up so well.

676
00:32:35,150 --> 00:32:37,050
High-five? High-five.

677
00:32:37,070 --> 00:32:38,850
[Ah, high-give!]

678
00:32:38,850 --> 00:32:41,330
They aren't in sync.

679
00:32:41,330 --> 00:32:45,490
Those two won't work together next time.

680
00:32:45,490 --> 00:32:47,950
I know. It's awkward.

681
00:32:48,050 --> 00:32:52,950
Team "Meet My Roommate" received 14 stops.

682
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:56,420
What was their average viewing time?

683
00:32:56,420 --> 00:32:58,480
- This is important, right?
- This is important.

684
00:32:58,480 --> 00:33:00,930
This is the decision maker.

685
00:33:00,930 --> 00:33:02,850
Right. This is important.

686
00:33:02,850 --> 00:33:04,390
Will it be revealed right now?

687
00:33:04,390 --> 00:33:09,030
Let's reveal it now.

688
00:33:10,430 --> 00:33:11,760
What could it be?

689
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:13,880
[Getting extra nervous, waiting for the result]

690
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:17,760
You received 14 stops.

691
00:33:17,760 --> 00:33:21,460
How many seconds is the average viewing time?

692
00:33:21,460 --> 00:33:22,990
I don't know what people are thinking.

693
00:33:22,990 --> 00:33:25,530
Since everything was shot in the house,

694
00:33:25,530 --> 00:33:29,590
they might find that a bit boring.

695
00:33:29,590 --> 00:33:31,530
That's what I'm worried about.

696
00:33:32,420 --> 00:33:35,730
I think placing the hook in the
beginning was a good call.

697
00:33:35,730 --> 00:33:38,320
Since Joo Seung acted well,

698
00:33:38,320 --> 00:33:41,110
I think we'll get a good result.

699
00:33:41,110 --> 00:33:43,120
[The video is 120 seconds long]

700
00:33:43,120 --> 00:33:44,700
How many seconds?

701
00:33:44,700 --> 00:33:46,770
[What is their average viewing time?]

702
00:33:49,550 --> 00:33:52,110
106.84 seconds.

703
00:33:52,940 --> 00:33:55,750
[It lasted over 100 seconds]

704
00:33:55,750 --> 00:33:58,310
- Is that long?
- I think it's not bad.

705
00:33:58,310 --> 00:34:00,070
That's really high.

706
00:34:00,070 --> 00:34:02,130
People basically watched until the end.

707
00:34:02,130 --> 00:34:03,510
That's a high number.

708
00:34:03,510 --> 00:34:05,370
What does this mean?

709
00:34:05,370 --> 00:34:07,060
- It sounds high.
- This means...

710
00:34:07,060 --> 00:34:09,230
they're currently in first place.

711
00:34:09,230 --> 00:34:10,530
Congratulations.

712
00:34:10,530 --> 00:34:11,960
[Currently in first place]

713
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:16,260
[Let's enjoy this while it lasts!]

714
00:34:16,260 --> 00:34:19,420
Since the viewing time is important,

715
00:34:19,420 --> 00:34:21,870
the time you spent contemplating
was meaningful.

716
00:34:21,870 --> 00:34:23,020
That's important!

717
00:34:23,020 --> 00:34:25,260
He watched it for a minute and 59 seconds.

718
00:34:25,260 --> 00:34:27,210
Right. That's what matters.

719
00:34:27,210 --> 00:34:30,350
Although we don't know about the stop count.

720
00:34:30,350 --> 00:34:33,110
If they get eliminated by a second,

721
00:34:33,110 --> 00:34:34,620
it'd be Cha Tae Hyun's fault.

722
00:34:34,620 --> 00:34:36,250
He's right. He's right.

723
00:34:36,250 --> 00:34:38,860
You think it's possible to get

724
00:34:38,860 --> 00:34:41,660
- the same exact score?
- That's your excuse?

725
00:34:41,660 --> 00:34:46,410
Director Lee Joo Seung, do you
think you'll stay in first place?

726
00:34:46,410 --> 00:34:48,740
I'm not sure if we'll stay in first place,

727
00:34:48,740 --> 00:34:52,790
but I'm happy about the viewing time.

728
00:34:52,790 --> 00:34:54,870
I think above 100 seconds is good.

729
00:34:54,870 --> 00:34:56,690
I have that feeling, too.

730
00:34:56,690 --> 00:35:00,790
[How long can they stay in first place?]

731
00:35:00,790 --> 00:35:03,340
Let's meet the next team.

732
00:35:03,340 --> 00:35:05,770
I wonder if they have good chemistry.

733
00:35:05,770 --> 00:35:09,500
The one-man creator and the novice director team.

734
00:35:09,500 --> 00:35:12,190
Team "Taste of Youth," please come forward.

735
00:35:12,190 --> 00:35:14,460
[How is the thumbnail?]

736
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:17,970
- It draws you in.
- It's pretty.

737
00:35:17,970 --> 00:35:19,660
I like the thumbnail.

738
00:35:19,660 --> 00:35:21,130
That's a nice photo.

739
00:35:21,130 --> 00:35:23,460
It's a simple plate of takoyaki.

740
00:35:23,460 --> 00:35:26,130
But with the title and everything,

741
00:35:26,130 --> 00:35:29,400
it makes you very curious.

742
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:33,130
We're two directors of the same age.

743
00:35:33,130 --> 00:35:35,820
We're Team "Taste of Youth."

744
00:35:36,710 --> 00:35:38,190
Team "Taste of Youth."

745
00:35:38,190 --> 00:35:39,710
Taste.

746
00:35:39,710 --> 00:35:45,620
I heard Kwon Sun Yong struggles to collaborate.

747
00:35:45,620 --> 00:35:47,250
That's right.

748
00:35:47,250 --> 00:35:50,220
I do cinematography, editing, audio,

749
00:35:50,220 --> 00:35:53,500
and lighting on my own. I set everything up.

750
00:35:53,500 --> 00:35:54,610
[All-rounder director, Kwon Sun Yong]

751
00:35:54,610 --> 00:35:55,970
That's just my personality.

752
00:35:55,970 --> 00:35:58,220
Even if it's lower quality,

753
00:35:58,220 --> 00:36:00,860
I feel more comfortable working on my own.

754
00:36:00,860 --> 00:36:03,650
I've always done that since I'm used to it.

755
00:36:03,650 --> 00:36:05,110
[The all-arounder Kwon Sun Yong's partner]

756
00:36:05,150 --> 00:36:09,620
Hello, I act, write,

757
00:36:09,620 --> 00:36:12,030
and I'm aspiring to become the short-form king.

758
00:36:12,030 --> 00:36:14,540
I'm Seo Jun Gyo, 32 years old. Nice to meet you.

759
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:17,750
How did you feel working together?

760
00:36:17,750 --> 00:36:20,220
When I heard we'll be co-directing,

761
00:36:20,220 --> 00:36:23,270
I was very worried even
before the mission started.

762
00:36:23,270 --> 00:36:24,830
But he's been so gracious.

763
00:36:24,830 --> 00:36:26,950
It went more easily than I expected.

764
00:36:26,950 --> 00:36:31,050
Your film crew was just two people?

765
00:36:31,050 --> 00:36:35,030
You two did everything on your own, then.

766
00:36:35,030 --> 00:36:38,810
Only Director Seo and I were on set.

767
00:36:38,810 --> 00:36:40,000
Two?

768
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,360
[Really? Just the two?]

769
00:36:41,700 --> 00:36:43,530
Let's start shooting right away.

770
00:36:43,530 --> 00:36:45,970
Action. Action. Action.

771
00:36:46,710 --> 00:36:49,240
[Only three people are on set]

772
00:36:49,240 --> 00:36:51,310
[All-rounder Kwon Sun Yong!]

773
00:36:51,310 --> 00:36:54,210
[Actor/director, Seo Jun Gyo!]

774
00:36:54,600 --> 00:36:57,910
[Totally DIY film set, very cost-effective!]

775
00:36:57,910 --> 00:37:00,980
You must've had spare budget, then.

776
00:37:00,980 --> 00:37:02,730
- Yes, we did.
- Really?

777
00:37:02,730 --> 00:37:04,550
What did you spend it on?

778
00:37:04,550 --> 00:37:05,800
- Did you buy food?
- Team dinner?

779
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:07,800
We split it in half.

780
00:37:07,800 --> 00:37:09,100
Really?

781
00:37:09,100 --> 00:37:11,610
- Can they do that?
- A profitable business.

782
00:37:11,610 --> 00:37:14,520
Wow, seriously?

783
00:37:14,520 --> 00:37:16,180
- Is that okay?
- I'm impressed.

784
00:37:16,180 --> 00:37:19,270
- Actually, the budget...
- The hidden item?

785
00:37:19,270 --> 00:37:22,140
We'll choose "Taste of Youth."

786
00:37:22,140 --> 00:37:27,080
Will "Taste of Youth" have a hidden item?

787
00:37:27,080 --> 00:37:28,740
Please reveal.

788
00:37:31,140 --> 00:37:32,050
[Taste of Youth]

789
00:37:32,050 --> 00:37:34,840
[Film equipment provided]

790
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:38,970
You'll be provided with a camera
and film equipment.

791
00:37:41,370 --> 00:37:44,400
[The hidden item for Team "Taste of Youth"]

792
00:37:44,770 --> 00:37:46,860
[Top-of-the-line film equipment]

793
00:37:47,300 --> 00:37:49,370
[In awe]

794
00:37:50,330 --> 00:37:52,210
[Happy]

795
00:37:52,650 --> 00:37:56,770
[Can feel the 7K quality]

796
00:37:56,770 --> 00:37:59,360
[They're already masters at heart!]

797
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:01,370
We're making a short-form drama.

798
00:38:01,370 --> 00:38:04,100
This shoots in 7K.

799
00:38:04,150 --> 00:38:05,740
If you shoot in the 3:2 ratio,

800
00:38:05,740 --> 00:38:07,250
you get both landscape and portrait orientations.

801
00:38:07,290 --> 00:38:11,020
You can film like this
without rotating the camera.

802
00:38:11,020 --> 00:38:12,630
How nice.

803
00:38:13,290 --> 00:38:16,350
[A high-quality camera
is the third member on set]

804
00:38:16,350 --> 00:38:19,150
Since we're adapting a webtoon about cooking,

805
00:38:19,150 --> 00:38:22,050
the food has to look delicious.

806
00:38:22,060 --> 00:38:26,160
Having a nice camera will help a lot.

807
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:29,750
Please introduce your work.

808
00:38:29,750 --> 00:38:33,150
We adapted a webtoon called "Taste of Youth."

809
00:38:33,150 --> 00:38:36,140
It's an episodic webtoon.

810
00:38:36,140 --> 00:38:39,160
It was tricky to choose the order.

811
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:42,790
[An episodic webtoon about young adults
relieving everyday stress through food]

812
00:38:42,790 --> 00:38:47,430
It's "Takoyaki Baby Love."
It's about a 20-year-old woman

813
00:38:47,430 --> 00:38:50,420
experiencing the first kiss of her life.

814
00:38:50,420 --> 00:38:53,050
With takoyaki as the subject...

815
00:38:53,050 --> 00:38:55,330
- First kiss?
- First kiss and takoyaki?

816
00:38:55,330 --> 00:38:59,580
Will Jun Gyo give her her first kiss, then?

817
00:38:59,580 --> 00:39:02,930
Please look forward to it.

818
00:39:02,930 --> 00:39:04,500
[Anticipating]

819
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:07,620
[Judging for "Taste of Youth" starts]

820
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:10,730
[What will happen to the directors born in '95?]

821
00:39:10,730 --> 00:39:12,900
Play the video.

822
00:39:13,500 --> 00:39:17,940
[Seo Jun Gyo and Kwon Sun Yong's
"Taste of Youth"]

823
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:22,760
Do I lack feminine charm?

824
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:24,670
Maybe he's just slow to act.

825
00:39:24,750 --> 00:39:27,240
- You said you held hands.
- What's the point?

826
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:29,700
Maybe he doesn't like me that much.

827
00:39:29,700 --> 00:39:32,630
Come on. Wait a bit.

828
00:39:32,630 --> 00:39:37,240
I'm actually visiting his apartment this Sunday.

829
00:39:37,240 --> 00:39:39,180
Huh? Really?

830
00:39:39,180 --> 00:39:41,780
- It's happening 100%.
- That looks good.

831
00:39:41,780 --> 00:39:44,070
Why are you visiting his apartment?

832
00:39:44,070 --> 00:39:47,140
He wants to make takoyaki together at home.

833
00:39:47,140 --> 00:39:48,920
Takoyaki?

834
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:51,510
He wants to make takoyaki together.

835
00:39:51,510 --> 00:39:53,470
Takoyaki?

836
00:39:53,470 --> 00:39:56,550
- Why are there so many?
- Should we eat outside?

837
00:39:56,550 --> 00:39:58,200
[Mixed feelings]

838
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:03,460
I'm at his apartment, but nothing is happening.

839
00:40:08,060 --> 00:40:11,460
What was I imagining?

840
00:40:11,460 --> 00:40:13,460
Don't you want any?

841
00:40:13,460 --> 00:40:15,420
I'll have one.

842
00:40:15,420 --> 00:40:18,140
The stop count is higher than I thought.

843
00:40:18,140 --> 00:40:19,250
What's the deal?

844
00:40:19,250 --> 00:40:22,320
Why so many stops? I'm surprised.

845
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:23,220
I'll have one.

846
00:40:23,220 --> 00:40:25,840
- Huh? No. Why?
- What was I imagining?

847
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:28,790
[People are asking for more dopamine hits!]

848
00:40:29,550 --> 00:40:31,550
It didn't work.

849
00:40:31,580 --> 00:40:35,200
I was like, "Let's prepare for the worst."

850
00:40:41,990 --> 00:40:44,650
It's way tastier than the restaurant kind.

851
00:40:44,650 --> 00:40:46,090
That's good.

852
00:40:46,090 --> 00:40:48,810
I noticed you like takoyaki.

853
00:40:48,810 --> 00:40:50,240
I actually...

854
00:40:51,440 --> 00:40:54,390
don't really like takoyaki.

855
00:40:54,390 --> 00:40:58,330
But if you really like him

856
00:40:58,330 --> 00:41:01,180
and if he likes you, too...

857
00:41:02,450 --> 00:41:04,130
[That's it]

858
00:41:04,130 --> 00:41:06,590
It's well-made. It was just the two of them.

859
00:41:07,190 --> 00:41:08,720
[Takoyaki date with Oppa]

860
00:41:10,490 --> 00:41:12,140
[Takoyaki with So Jeong]

861
00:41:14,330 --> 00:41:16,230
Just go for it.

862
00:41:16,230 --> 00:41:18,730
It doesn't matter who does it first.

863
00:41:18,730 --> 00:41:22,990
My first kiss tastes like takoyaki.

864
00:41:22,990 --> 00:41:25,560
[The kiss ending added two more votes]

865
00:41:25,560 --> 00:41:27,360
[31 stops in total]

866
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:28,890
A lot of votes.

867
00:41:28,890 --> 00:41:30,490
Why so many...

868
00:41:30,490 --> 00:41:34,260
I was absorbed and realized it was over 20.

869
00:41:34,260 --> 00:41:38,480
We're getting a lot more stops than before.

870
00:41:38,480 --> 00:41:40,790
[Everyone is getting quiet]

871
00:41:40,790 --> 00:41:43,600
I liked it a lot.

872
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:47,990
What do you think? You got 31 stops.

873
00:41:47,990 --> 00:41:52,650
Yes, it's higher than expected.

874
00:41:52,650 --> 00:41:54,600
I'm a bit mad right now.

875
00:41:55,320 --> 00:41:56,510
I'm a bit mad right now.

876
00:41:56,510 --> 00:41:57,780
[Hehe]

877
00:41:57,780 --> 00:41:59,620
Right.

878
00:41:59,620 --> 00:42:04,590
Directors can't help but be mad at the audience.

879
00:42:04,590 --> 00:42:06,120
It's a love-hate relationship.

880
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:09,320
When "Be Melodramatic" got 1% ratings,
I hated the world.

881
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:11,530
- It got 1%?
- Yes.

882
00:42:11,530 --> 00:42:12,720
Yes.

883
00:42:12,720 --> 00:42:14,840
[The 10-million director's sad period]

884
00:42:14,840 --> 00:42:16,730
[Sad cast member of "Be Melodramatic"]

885
00:42:16,730 --> 00:42:19,830
- But the ratings aren't everything.
- True.

886
00:42:19,830 --> 00:42:21,690
[Still upset]

887
00:42:21,690 --> 00:42:25,300
The format was like a teaser,

888
00:42:25,300 --> 00:42:28,960
but the pacing was of an hour-long drama.

889
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:31,080
It was quite slow.

890
00:42:31,080 --> 00:42:33,870
I think the 31 people agree.

891
00:42:33,870 --> 00:42:39,090
I think they voted because it missed that mark.

892
00:42:39,090 --> 00:42:43,940
If you're someone who watches
a lot of short dramas,

893
00:42:43,940 --> 00:42:46,140
you'll understand why it got 31 votes.

894
00:42:46,140 --> 00:42:49,350
It was a little boring toward the middle.

895
00:42:49,350 --> 00:42:51,220
- They voted because they couldn't stand it.
- I know.

896
00:42:51,220 --> 00:42:53,250
Short dramas are so tough.

897
00:42:53,250 --> 00:42:57,220
Team "Taste of Youth" got 31 stops.

898
00:42:57,220 --> 00:43:01,510
Let's check their average viewing time.

899
00:43:01,510 --> 00:43:04,880
The current first-place team is
Team Lee Dong Hun and Lee Joo Seung.

900
00:43:04,950 --> 00:43:09,350
Will there be a change in ranking?
Let's see the result.

901
00:43:09,410 --> 00:43:11,950
[What would happen?]

902
00:43:12,600 --> 00:43:14,530
What's the point?

903
00:43:15,230 --> 00:43:18,570
Do you go up if your viewing time is longer?

904
00:43:19,910 --> 00:43:21,430
What could it be?

905
00:43:21,430 --> 00:43:24,450
How will the number of stops affect this?

906
00:43:24,450 --> 00:43:27,600
[Their average viewing time was 106.84 seconds]

907
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:29,660
[The result for "Taste of Youth"]

908
00:43:31,650 --> 00:43:34,320
[81.54 seconds]

909
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:36,310
Gosh, look at that.

910
00:43:36,310 --> 00:43:37,460
It was 81.54 seconds.

911
00:43:37,460 --> 00:43:40,080
[About a minute and 20 seconds]

912
00:43:40,080 --> 00:43:43,580
It was 81.54 seconds.

913
00:43:43,580 --> 00:43:45,310
[Currently in second place]

914
00:43:45,310 --> 00:43:47,830
What do you think? Are you
satisfied with the result?

915
00:43:47,830 --> 00:43:50,620
- I have no regrets.
- I should be satisfied.

916
00:43:50,620 --> 00:43:52,370
You're still in second place. You never know.

917
00:43:52,370 --> 00:43:54,200
That's right. You never know.

918
00:43:54,200 --> 00:43:57,540
Directors Seo Jun Gyo and
Kwon Sun Yong, thank you.

919
00:43:57,540 --> 00:44:00,380
Please go back to your seats.

920
00:44:00,380 --> 00:44:03,250
- Thank you.
- Good work.

921
00:44:04,080 --> 00:44:05,910
It's time to welcome the next team.

922
00:44:05,910 --> 00:44:09,220
I'm kind of curious about this team.

923
00:44:09,220 --> 00:44:11,300
- Which team?
- As a dad.

924
00:44:11,300 --> 00:44:15,000
They're like an uncle and nieces.

925
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:17,080
The team on a broadcasting station tour?

926
00:44:17,080 --> 00:44:20,060
Team "After School," please come out.

927
00:44:20,060 --> 00:44:22,540
Fighting, Teacher! Fighting, Teacher!

928
00:44:22,540 --> 00:44:25,220
He's dressed like a teacher, too.

929
00:44:25,220 --> 00:44:29,210
- So cute.
- Wow, what's this?

930
00:44:29,210 --> 00:44:32,740
"After School" is a mystery thriller
about male students

931
00:44:32,740 --> 00:44:35,300
who get involved with unexpected events.

932
00:44:35,300 --> 00:44:38,140
- Huh?
- What's going on with the font?

933
00:44:38,140 --> 00:44:39,700
It's dripping down.

934
00:44:39,700 --> 00:44:41,720
Hold on. Something's dripping.

935
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:43,400
Wow, this is...

936
00:44:43,400 --> 00:44:45,940
Right, this is an action mystery.

937
00:44:45,940 --> 00:44:48,140
[Dying to know]

938
00:44:48,140 --> 00:44:50,130
Hello.

939
00:44:51,170 --> 00:44:53,150
I thought we were chanting.

940
00:44:53,150 --> 00:44:55,530
This team is too cute.

941
00:44:55,530 --> 00:44:58,990
Hello, we're Team "10 Million-Volt."

942
00:44:58,990 --> 00:45:01,300
[Cute/Sour]

943
00:45:01,300 --> 00:45:03,370
[Awkward]

944
00:45:03,370 --> 00:45:06,510
There's a stranger among them.

945
00:45:06,510 --> 00:45:10,390
The name of their club is "Million-Volt."

946
00:45:10,390 --> 00:45:12,740
But it's "10 Million-Volt" because I joined them.

947
00:45:12,740 --> 00:45:14,930
How exciting.

948
00:45:14,930 --> 00:45:19,260
Hello, I'm a comedy director, Kim Dong Ha.

949
00:45:19,260 --> 00:45:20,750
[His black comedy "Stand Up Love"]

950
00:45:20,750 --> 00:45:24,270
People's urine started turning green.

951
00:45:24,270 --> 00:45:26,990
The editing was a bit slow.

952
00:45:26,990 --> 00:45:29,270
I've never made a short drama before.

953
00:45:29,270 --> 00:45:32,750
I'll work harder now that I know better.

954
00:45:32,750 --> 00:45:38,230
I heard the filmmaking club
gives you free tteokbokki.

955
00:45:38,230 --> 00:45:40,150
That's how everything starts.

956
00:45:40,150 --> 00:45:44,050
[Mystery school fantasy,
"Unfinished Film, Now Playing"]

957
00:45:44,480 --> 00:45:47,160
[Different genre, different age.
How did they form a team?]

958
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:50,930
I heard you met up after school,
just like the title.

959
00:45:50,930 --> 00:45:53,890
Since we have school every day...

960
00:45:53,890 --> 00:45:55,640
Oh, that's right.

961
00:45:55,640 --> 00:45:57,630
Director Kim was very considerate of us.

962
00:45:57,630 --> 00:46:01,500
We had weekday evening meetings via Zoom.

963
00:46:01,500 --> 00:46:04,000
[Zoom meetings at 8 p.m. on weekdays]

964
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:06,080
Since we live in very different environments,

965
00:46:06,080 --> 00:46:08,120
we had to find a way to work together.

966
00:46:08,120 --> 00:46:10,490
We decided to talk a lot, at least.

967
00:46:10,490 --> 00:46:12,350
What should we name the dog?

968
00:46:12,350 --> 00:46:14,550
Park Myung Soo.

969
00:46:14,550 --> 00:46:16,880
- Park Myung Soo?
- Let's do that. I like it.

970
00:46:16,880 --> 00:46:19,020
[Park Myung Soo, it is]

971
00:46:19,020 --> 00:46:24,090
Looks like you had to work with many limitations.

972
00:46:24,090 --> 00:46:25,580
There probably were limitations,

973
00:46:25,580 --> 00:46:29,270
but Director Kim and the rest of the team

974
00:46:29,270 --> 00:46:31,270
has an age gap of 18 years.

975
00:46:31,270 --> 00:46:33,870
You must've had different sensibilities.

976
00:46:33,870 --> 00:46:36,060
I'm so curious. How did you overcome it?

977
00:46:36,060 --> 00:46:38,910
I started college in 2010.

978
00:46:38,910 --> 00:46:42,970
The youngest, Shin Yul, was born in 2011.

979
00:46:42,970 --> 00:46:46,720
My father is 20 years older than I am.

980
00:46:46,720 --> 00:46:49,470
I thought of my father and...

981
00:46:49,470 --> 00:46:51,960
[Suddenly decided to become a father]

982
00:46:51,960 --> 00:46:53,860
That's so filial of you.

983
00:46:53,860 --> 00:46:55,420
[I understand how he must've felt now]

984
00:46:55,420 --> 00:46:57,070
But that's why.

985
00:46:57,070 --> 00:46:59,650
I heard Hae On and her friends were

986
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:02,880
all about being provocative.

987
00:47:02,880 --> 00:47:04,800
How were you provocative?

988
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:07,740
Since we're young,

989
00:47:07,740 --> 00:47:12,410
Director Kim suggested
removing the shocking scenes.

990
00:47:12,410 --> 00:47:16,170
But we wanted to make the original work shine.

991
00:47:16,170 --> 00:47:20,430
So, we insisted on keeping them.
That's what happened.

992
00:47:20,430 --> 00:47:23,230
Why is Director Kim shaking his head?

993
00:47:23,230 --> 00:47:25,080
It's not good for them.

994
00:47:25,080 --> 00:47:26,660
[Hehe]

995
00:47:28,250 --> 00:47:31,190
But we have to win.

996
00:47:31,190 --> 00:47:32,410
[What were their film sets like?]

997
00:47:32,450 --> 00:47:35,150
He became their teacher.

998
00:47:35,170 --> 00:47:38,250
Ready. Ready. Ready.

999
00:47:38,250 --> 00:47:39,640
Action.

1000
00:47:39,650 --> 00:47:42,750
["After School" shooting location]

1001
00:47:42,760 --> 00:47:44,780
Cut.

1002
00:47:45,870 --> 00:47:48,710
We can't work if you both
play the director's role.

1003
00:47:48,710 --> 00:47:51,360
Only one of you will.

1004
00:47:51,360 --> 00:47:54,490
It looks like I'm doing a lot,

1005
00:47:54,490 --> 00:47:57,610
but I ask the girls' opinions.

1006
00:47:57,610 --> 00:47:59,080
Not bad, right?

1007
00:47:59,080 --> 00:48:00,920
Can we add anything?

1008
00:48:00,920 --> 00:48:04,470
[Collaborating hard]

1009
00:48:04,470 --> 00:48:06,910
You're holding the hammer like this.

1010
00:48:06,910 --> 00:48:10,120
I thought that if we combined my resources

1011
00:48:10,120 --> 00:48:13,950
with their ideas, it'd be fun.

1012
00:48:13,950 --> 00:48:18,570
Dong Ha, Yun Seo, and I took turns to monitor.

1013
00:48:18,570 --> 00:48:21,330
[Oh Hae On is the director of the first half]

1014
00:48:21,330 --> 00:48:23,260
I think it's slightly out of focus.

1015
00:48:23,260 --> 00:48:25,340
Okay, I'll redo it.

1016
00:48:25,340 --> 00:48:29,110
I think you could duck a lot more at the end.

1017
00:48:29,110 --> 00:48:31,460
[Ra Yun Seo directs the latter half]

1018
00:48:31,460 --> 00:48:34,320
When will I get to work with students again?

1019
00:48:34,320 --> 00:48:37,540
It feels like I'm an instructor
at a youth filmmaking camp.

1020
00:48:37,540 --> 00:48:41,720
Slow it down by 1.5 times in your head.

1021
00:48:41,720 --> 00:48:42,970
It's fun, isn't it?

1022
00:48:42,970 --> 00:48:44,730
- Say it's fun.
- It's fun.

1023
00:48:44,730 --> 00:48:46,060
Of course it is.

1024
00:48:46,060 --> 00:48:49,030
When I heard I'll be directing with them,

1025
00:48:49,030 --> 00:48:50,730
I had this thought.

1026
00:48:50,730 --> 00:48:54,970
I wanted them to experience a good environment.

1027
00:48:54,970 --> 00:49:00,060
It's a competition, but it's still about people.

1028
00:49:00,060 --> 00:49:02,630
We were really like a teacher and students.

1029
00:49:02,630 --> 00:49:05,190
It was a great opportunity to learn a lot.

1030
00:49:05,190 --> 00:49:07,140
I thought it was great.

1031
00:49:07,140 --> 00:49:08,740
- Hello.
- Hello.

1032
00:49:08,740 --> 00:49:12,490
[The secret weapon of Team "After School"]

1033
00:49:12,490 --> 00:49:15,120
Hello, I'm actor Lee Shin Ki.

1034
00:49:15,120 --> 00:49:16,750
Nice to meet you.

1035
00:49:16,750 --> 00:49:20,280
I'm a friend of Director Kim Dong Ha.

1036
00:49:20,280 --> 00:49:21,920
That's how I got to participate.

1037
00:49:21,920 --> 00:49:23,630
[The thriller vibe is dominating the set]

1038
00:49:23,630 --> 00:49:26,800
[A scene stealer with crazy acting skills]

1039
00:49:26,800 --> 00:49:28,910
That's nice.

1040
00:49:28,910 --> 00:49:30,440
Are you sure it is, Director?

1041
00:49:30,440 --> 00:49:32,200
I love it.

1042
00:49:32,200 --> 00:49:34,790
Let's say "Thank you" and move on to the next.

1043
00:49:34,790 --> 00:49:36,670
One, two, three.

1044
00:49:36,670 --> 00:49:38,670
Thank you.

1045
00:49:38,670 --> 00:49:41,580
[How did "After School" turn out?]

1046
00:49:41,580 --> 00:49:44,310
Please introduce your work.

1047
00:49:44,310 --> 00:49:47,340
Using Million-Volt's teen sensibility,

1048
00:49:47,340 --> 00:49:49,720
we depicted quarrels after school

1049
00:49:49,720 --> 00:49:52,280
and heart-warming friendships.

1050
00:49:52,280 --> 00:49:57,230
But then the main characters
also get involved in an incident.

1051
00:49:57,250 --> 00:50:01,150
It's also a mystery story
with a thriller sensibility.

1052
00:50:01,150 --> 00:50:02,430
I'm curious.

1053
00:50:02,430 --> 00:50:03,950
I'm so curious.

1054
00:50:03,950 --> 00:50:06,760
Gosh, I can't wait.

1055
00:50:06,760 --> 00:50:08,800
[Right before the video starts]

1056
00:50:08,800 --> 00:50:11,110
- Guys.
- Like this.

1057
00:50:11,110 --> 00:50:13,630
- Let's check at the end.
- Okay.

1058
00:50:14,550 --> 00:50:18,150
Play the video.

1059
00:50:18,970 --> 00:50:21,560
I think I was extra nervous.

1060
00:50:21,560 --> 00:50:23,660
Since I've done this before,

1061
