1200
00:57:10,950 --> 00:57:17,750
Whether you can go past 100 seconds
or not would be the key.

1201
00:57:17,790 --> 00:57:19,760
What do we do?

1202
00:57:19,760 --> 00:57:21,670
What do you guys think?

1203
00:57:21,670 --> 00:57:22,860
You're in second place.

1204
00:57:22,860 --> 00:57:26,810
To be honest, I'm not totally satisfied.

1205
00:57:26,810 --> 00:57:29,360
I'm a bit disappointed.

1206
00:57:29,360 --> 00:57:31,440
To be very honest,

1207
00:57:31,440 --> 00:57:33,950
ours was good. It was good.

1208
00:57:33,950 --> 00:57:36,840
Were the boring moments in the beginning?

1209
00:57:36,840 --> 00:57:40,880
I wonder if we should've
introduced the twist earlier,

1210
00:57:40,880 --> 00:57:45,690
but I'm very satisfied with the product.

1211
00:57:45,690 --> 00:57:47,740
So, I'm not sure.

1212
00:57:47,740 --> 00:57:50,620
Everyone is better than I expected.

1213
00:57:50,620 --> 00:57:52,350
Everyone is so good.

1214
00:57:52,350 --> 00:57:54,700
Maybe my expectation was too low.

1215
00:57:54,700 --> 00:57:56,840
Is it our turn now?

1216
00:57:57,640 --> 00:58:00,730
- Another romance?
- Romance and thriller, probably.

1217
00:58:00,730 --> 00:58:02,210
Whose turn is it next?

1218
00:58:02,210 --> 00:58:06,520
I'm very excited about these
two directors teaming up.

1219
00:58:06,520 --> 00:58:08,790
- Which team?
- They're so unique.

1220
00:58:08,790 --> 00:58:12,100
Team "Black Out Girl Hanami," come forward.

1221
00:58:12,100 --> 00:58:14,290
[Meeting of master of absurd humor
and visual master]

1222
00:58:14,290 --> 00:58:16,150
Oh, this team?

1223
00:58:16,150 --> 00:58:17,320
I'm most excited for this team.

1224
00:58:17,320 --> 00:58:20,930
This is a controversial team.

1225
00:58:23,330 --> 00:58:26,170
It's funny that they got this far.

1226
00:58:26,170 --> 00:58:28,100
They haven't fought yet.

1227
00:58:28,100 --> 00:58:30,320
[Han Sang Il's "My Love Story
Only I Don't Know About"]

1228
00:58:30,320 --> 00:58:33,630
[Jeong Joo's "No Humans"
with great cinematography]

1229
00:58:34,180 --> 00:58:36,940
[Two directors with distinctive styles]

1230
00:58:36,940 --> 00:58:39,390
I'm so curious how you worked together.

1231
00:58:39,390 --> 00:58:42,350
They're really something, too.

1232
00:58:42,350 --> 00:58:43,520
Look at the poster.

1233
00:58:43,520 --> 00:58:45,560
[The bubbly and goofy thumbnail]

1234
00:58:45,560 --> 00:58:52,050
[A story about a girl who passes out
in front of the man she likes]

1235
00:58:52,050 --> 00:58:54,680
- I like the poster.
- Me, too.

1236
00:58:54,680 --> 00:58:56,260
It's so eye-catching.

1237
00:58:56,260 --> 00:58:59,330
The arrow went through her ears.

1238
00:58:59,330 --> 00:59:01,560
[Eye-catching thumbnail]

1239
00:59:01,560 --> 00:59:03,590
- Absurd humor.
- Visual.

1240
00:59:03,590 --> 00:59:05,530
- We're the best.
- We're the best.

1241
00:59:05,530 --> 00:59:06,670
[Forbidden bromance]

1242
00:59:06,670 --> 00:59:08,460
It's so hard to watch.

1243
00:59:08,460 --> 00:59:10,080
[Get used to it]

1244
00:59:10,080 --> 00:59:11,270
[LOL]

1245
00:59:11,270 --> 00:59:12,580
[Proud of himself]

1246
00:59:12,580 --> 00:59:16,990
Did you practice that just now?

1247
00:59:16,990 --> 00:59:18,500
About seven times?

1248
00:59:18,500 --> 00:59:20,640
You practiced?

1249
00:59:20,640 --> 00:59:21,900
That's surprising.

1250
00:59:21,900 --> 00:59:24,080
I couldn't let myself practice.

1251
00:59:24,080 --> 00:59:26,830
Right. It's definitely not your style.

1252
00:59:26,830 --> 00:59:29,790
You're so different already.

1253
00:59:29,790 --> 00:59:31,150
Tell us about your roles.

1254
00:59:31,150 --> 00:59:34,820
How did you decide on your roles on set?

1255
00:59:34,820 --> 00:59:36,840
["Black Out Girl Hanami" set in Mapo-gu]

1256
00:59:36,840 --> 00:59:37,810
[Class motto]

1257
00:59:38,160 --> 00:59:40,070
[The shooting is about to start]

1258
00:59:40,070 --> 00:59:42,500
[Director Han Sang Il arrived early]

1259
00:59:42,500 --> 00:59:45,950
I immediately said, "You're the
cinematographer, and I'm the screenwriter."

1260
00:59:45,950 --> 00:59:48,400
He did everything on his own.

1261
00:59:48,400 --> 00:59:50,110
We haven't had disagreements.

1262
00:59:50,110 --> 00:59:52,330
But I'm not sure how today will go.

1263
00:59:52,330 --> 00:59:54,180
[Pacing around]

1264
00:59:54,440 --> 00:59:56,830
[Busy setting up for the shoot]

1265
00:59:56,830 --> 00:59:58,770
It's because of the depth.

1266
00:59:58,770 --> 01:00:01,050
We aren't getting the depth.

1267
01:00:01,050 --> 01:00:04,150
Because we split duties,
I think we'll work together well.

1268
01:00:04,180 --> 01:00:08,730
Sang Il and I have very different styles.

1269
01:00:09,720 --> 01:00:11,450
We direct in different ways, too.

1270
01:00:11,450 --> 01:00:15,520
I think we'll have good synergy.

1271
01:00:15,520 --> 01:00:17,880
[Jeong Joo is working hard for better visuals]

1272
01:00:18,920 --> 01:00:21,430
It's nice not to do hard labor like that.

1273
01:00:21,430 --> 01:00:23,380
[Working hard to improve the visuals]

1274
01:00:23,380 --> 01:00:26,480
We have to fill the screen
because it's in portrait.

1275
01:00:26,480 --> 01:00:28,780
- Did you get some sleep?
- Yes.

1276
01:00:28,780 --> 01:00:31,010
- I don't think you did.
- I did.

1277
01:00:31,010 --> 01:00:32,570
[My precious film crew]

1278
01:00:32,570 --> 01:00:34,370
I told you to get some sleep.

1279
01:00:34,370 --> 01:00:36,490
That's enough.

1280
01:00:36,490 --> 01:00:40,000
- I didn't think we'd be delayed.
- What?

1281
01:00:40,000 --> 01:00:42,640
The film crew should be the first
ones here. Why are they late?

1282
01:00:42,640 --> 01:00:44,020
I know.

1283
01:00:44,560 --> 01:00:46,820
[Worried]

1284
01:00:47,280 --> 01:00:49,530
[The camera is getting set up later than planned]

1285
01:00:49,530 --> 01:00:53,070
We were supposed to shoot the
first scene in 10 minutes.

1286
01:00:53,070 --> 01:00:56,300
We don't get good results
when the film crew is nervous.

1287
01:00:56,300 --> 01:00:59,300
Give us 30 minutes.

1288
01:00:59,300 --> 01:01:02,320
Film crew, take your time.

1289
01:01:02,320 --> 01:01:05,280
Don't be nervous. You have 30 minutes.

1290
01:01:05,280 --> 01:01:06,830
It happens.

1291
01:01:06,830 --> 01:01:09,050
Delays are crucial on set.

1292
01:01:09,050 --> 01:01:10,970
[Just staring at Jeong Joo]

1293
01:01:11,530 --> 01:01:13,710
[Things got more hectic due to the delay]

1294
01:01:13,710 --> 01:01:16,950
Where can I monitor?
You haven't set it up yet, right?

1295
01:01:16,950 --> 01:01:20,360
