1296
01:01:20,360 --> 01:01:22,350
[30 minutes later]

1297
01:01:22,780 --> 01:01:24,860
We have to start now.

1298
01:01:24,860 --> 01:01:26,390
Check the monitor right now.

1299
01:01:26,390 --> 01:01:28,700
Hurry up, guys.

1300
01:01:28,700 --> 01:01:30,430
Guys.

1301
01:01:30,430 --> 01:01:32,850
Bring one and start already.

1302
01:01:32,850 --> 01:01:34,140
What's the deal?

1303
01:01:34,140 --> 01:01:36,400
[Clumsy]

1304
01:01:37,050 --> 01:01:39,230
This is a disaster. The worst.

1305
01:01:39,910 --> 01:01:42,320
They didn't set things up.

1306
01:01:43,670 --> 01:01:45,400
[Chaos]

1307
01:01:45,770 --> 01:01:47,940
[Can they shoot the first scene today?]

1308
01:01:47,940 --> 01:01:49,610
Three minutes.

1309
01:01:51,820 --> 01:01:54,820
The shooting was delayed a bit.

1310
01:01:55,810 --> 01:01:57,900
[Were they able to shoot as planned?]

1311
01:01:57,900 --> 01:02:00,360
Let me be a bit harsh.

1312
01:02:00,360 --> 01:02:02,590
Let me be a bit harsh.

1313
01:02:02,590 --> 01:02:04,620
Finally.

1314
01:02:04,620 --> 01:02:07,930
Director Han Sang Il,

1315
01:02:07,930 --> 01:02:11,230
you're the kind of director actors hate the most.

1316
01:02:11,230 --> 01:02:12,900
Why is that?

1317
01:02:12,900 --> 01:02:14,940
Why? Why?

1318
01:02:14,940 --> 01:02:16,750
[Glaring]

1319
01:02:16,750 --> 01:02:22,210
I heard you change the finalized
storyboard on set all the time.

1320
01:02:22,210 --> 01:02:25,430
- Gosh.
- You change it all the time.

1321
01:02:25,430 --> 01:02:27,840
How can you explain that?

1322
01:02:27,840 --> 01:02:31,830
If I say this, I might sound
a bit like "that."

1323
01:02:31,830 --> 01:02:34,690
- I think you are.
- What's "that"? A jerk?

1324
01:02:34,750 --> 01:02:37,650
- He is "that."
- You are.

1325
01:02:37,650 --> 01:02:40,390
Can you use that? Geez.

1326
01:02:40,390 --> 01:02:43,910
I can't keep up. What's going on?

1327
01:02:43,910 --> 01:02:46,710
I've always wanted to direct while lying down.

1328
01:02:46,710 --> 01:02:49,650
[Shooting from a new angle is okay]

1329
01:02:49,650 --> 01:02:51,900
Either the actor turns, or the camera turns.

1330
01:02:51,900 --> 01:02:54,200
Get out of the scene. Show the background.

1331
01:02:54,200 --> 01:02:55,270
Cut.

1332
01:02:55,270 --> 01:02:57,120
[Voice-over is okay]

1333
01:02:57,120 --> 01:02:59,060
I'm thinking of doing voice-over.

1334
01:02:59,150 --> 01:03:01,450
[Rethinking the storyboard in his head]

1335
01:03:01,450 --> 01:03:04,060
I'm fully counting on Sang Il.

1336
01:03:04,060 --> 01:03:07,390
- The storyboard keeps changing.
- Just trust me.

1337
01:03:09,160 --> 01:03:11,510
The second person comes in. Go.

1338
01:03:11,510 --> 01:03:13,590
[I'm dying...]

1339
01:03:14,050 --> 01:03:17,440
[Stuck on Han Sang Il's "action" loop]

1340
01:03:17,440 --> 01:03:21,130
I tell the actor to do things
the way they're best at.

1341
01:03:21,130 --> 01:03:23,120
That's my style.

1342
01:03:23,150 --> 01:03:27,450
If you can express it better than
what I wrote, just go with that.

1343
01:03:27,450 --> 01:03:29,010
"Try it if you will."

1344
01:03:29,010 --> 01:03:31,600
I change the lines based on the way they talk.

1345
01:03:31,600 --> 01:03:32,700
I stand corrected.

1346
01:03:32,700 --> 01:03:34,890
You might be the kind of director actors love.

1347
01:03:34,890 --> 01:03:37,330
- You're right.
- I object.

1348
01:03:37,330 --> 01:03:39,160
He objects!

1349
01:03:39,160 --> 01:03:41,170
Since I did the pre-production,

1350
01:03:41,170 --> 01:03:45,950
I managed the cast, sets, and crew.

1351
01:03:45,950 --> 01:03:50,100
But Director Han kept switching to freestyle.

1352
01:03:50,100 --> 01:03:52,350
They all look at me whenever things change.

1353
01:03:52,350 --> 01:03:53,720
The actors, too.

1354
01:03:53,720 --> 01:03:55,390
He didn't even come to the reading.

1355
01:03:55,390 --> 01:03:57,650
[Is a fight erupting?]

1356
01:03:57,650 --> 01:03:58,820
[Where's the popcorn?]

1357
01:03:58,820 --> 01:04:03,100
They don't seem to get along, but they do.

1358
01:04:03,100 --> 01:04:06,560
I thought it'd be one or the other.

1359
01:04:06,560 --> 01:04:09,040
"Black Out Girl Hanami" is

1360
01:04:09,040 --> 01:04:14,230
about Hanami, who had a traumatic relationship.

1361
01:04:14,230 --> 01:04:16,580
When she confesses her love to her crush,

1362
01:04:16,650 --> 01:04:20,550
her heart rate increases too much,
and she passes out.

1363
01:04:20,550 --> 01:04:24,750
It's about her finding love
while overcoming her challenge.

1364
01:04:24,750 --> 01:04:29,450
There are double nosebleeds, knee smash,

1365
01:04:29,450 --> 01:04:31,670
and flying through the window scene.

1366
01:04:31,670 --> 01:04:33,780
I couldn't have come up with those myself.

1367
01:04:33,780 --> 01:04:35,830
It was fun.

1368
01:04:35,830 --> 01:04:37,150
Let us win first place.

1369
01:04:37,150 --> 01:04:39,030
The die has been thrown already.

1370
01:04:39,030 --> 01:04:40,930
May the other teams fail.

1371
01:04:40,930 --> 01:04:42,370
Fail!

1372
01:04:42,370 --> 01:04:43,870
Fail!

1373
01:04:44,730 --> 01:04:47,020
Let's start the judging now.

1374
01:04:47,020 --> 01:04:49,430
Play the video.

1375
01:04:49,430 --> 01:04:52,650
[The moment of truth]

1376
01:04:53,170 --> 01:04:55,590
I'll watch like a hawk.

1377
01:04:56,330 --> 01:04:58,330
[Black Out Girl Hanami]

1378
01:04:58,330 --> 01:05:02,150
Hanami left to confess her love
to the student president.

1379
01:05:03,120 --> 01:05:05,110
Hey, Hanami!

1380
01:05:05,110 --> 01:05:07,320
Stop right there!

1381
01:05:08,360 --> 01:05:10,220
This is no good.

1382
01:05:11,090 --> 01:05:12,480
Oh, my God.

1383
01:05:12,480 --> 01:05:14,310
Sunbae,

1384
01:05:14,310 --> 01:05:17,330
I think I fell in...

1385
01:05:20,450 --> 01:05:22,870
You think I'm crazy? Why would I like you?

1386
01:05:22,870 --> 01:05:25,710
Who would like someone like you?

1387
01:05:25,710 --> 01:05:28,750
This is not going to work.

1388
01:05:30,670 --> 01:05:31,950
Are you okay?

1389
01:05:31,950 --> 01:05:33,870
You've been looking pale since earlier.

1390
01:05:33,870 --> 01:05:36,460
No, he's too close.

1391
01:05:37,280 --> 01:05:39,490
I think I f...

1392
01:05:40,620 --> 01:05:43,560
No, Hanami! Don't confess your love!

1393
01:05:43,650 --> 01:05:47,750
I think I fell... I f... f*** you.

1394
01:05:53,260 --> 01:05:56,590
Did she say "f*** you"?

1395
01:05:56,590 --> 01:05:58,360
[LOL]

1396
01:05:58,360 --> 01:06:00,760
[The stop count and the reception look good]

1397
01:06:06,030 --> 01:06:09,530
Did it happen again?

1398
01:06:12,780 --> 01:06:14,720
Min Ho?

1399
01:06:15,380 --> 01:06:18,280
Min Ho, don't go!

1400
01:06:19,370 --> 01:06:22,980
I have a trauma from the past.

1401
01:06:22,980 --> 01:06:26,150
When I see or touch someone I like,

1402
01:06:26,150 --> 01:06:28,880
I pass out like I did today.

1403
01:06:29,870 --> 01:06:32,940
[The stop count is rising as soon
as the pacing slows down]

1404
01:06:32,940 --> 01:06:36,280
I added my flair briefly in the middle.
It's a long-take shot.

1405
01:06:36,350 --> 01:06:39,250
I don't think we needed it.
I should've edited it at this speed.

1406
01:06:39,260 --> 01:06:43,100
The tempo should've been
like this when she got up.

1407
01:06:43,100 --> 01:06:46,680
I have a trauma from the past.

1408
01:06:46,680 --> 01:06:49,910
When I see or touch someone I like,

1409
01:06:49,910 --> 01:06:52,510
I pass out like I did today.

1410
01:06:52,510 --> 01:06:54,690
So...

1411
01:06:54,690 --> 01:06:57,900
don't go. Be by my side-

1412
01:06:58,830 --> 01:07:00,730
[Kay, idol star]

1413
01:07:00,730 --> 01:07:03,040
What are you doing here?

1414
01:07:03,040 --> 01:07:06,670
- Do you like Do Min Ho?
- Don't say it! Don't say it!

1415
01:07:07,680 --> 01:07:09,660
Want to know a secret?

1416
01:07:09,660 --> 01:07:11,680
Your crush Do Min Ho...

1417
01:07:12,950 --> 01:07:15,360
He's my brother's killer.

1418
01:07:17,370 --> 01:07:22,080
Min Ho is a killer?

1419
01:07:23,360 --> 01:07:26,140
[You can watch the full version on Lehzin Snack]

1420
01:07:26,140 --> 01:07:28,640
Well done.

1421
01:07:28,640 --> 01:07:29,870
Give me more!

1422
01:07:29,870 --> 01:07:31,940
Give me more! Give me more!

1423
01:07:31,940 --> 01:07:35,710
There's excitement in the studio right now.

1424
01:07:35,710 --> 01:07:37,690
- Wow.
- Give me more.

1425
01:07:37,690 --> 01:07:38,850
It's driving me crazy.

1426
01:07:38,850 --> 01:07:42,620
The stop count is the lowest so far.

1427
01:07:42,620 --> 01:07:46,840
It was the most perfect first
episode we've seen so far.

1428
01:07:46,840 --> 01:07:49,740
It was just the way I like it.

1429
01:07:49,740 --> 01:07:52,300
I loved the comedic moments, too.

1430
01:07:52,300 --> 01:07:55,340
When something is outside your expectation,

1431
01:07:55,340 --> 01:07:56,840
you find it much more alluring.

1432
01:07:56,850 --> 01:08:02,530
The actors and the visuals are so pretty,

1433
01:08:02,530 --> 01:08:05,160
but we kept seeing funny moments.

1434
01:08:05,160 --> 01:08:06,810
- This is...
- It was powerful.

1435
01:08:06,810 --> 01:08:09,790
Director Han Sang Il's absurd humor

1436
01:08:09,790 --> 01:08:13,550
and Director Jeong Joo's cinematography

1437
01:08:13,550 --> 01:08:16,830
created a perfect combination.

1438
01:08:16,830 --> 01:08:19,760
The absurd humor trumps everything.

1439
01:08:19,760 --> 01:08:21,250
It's not easy to do.

1440
01:08:21,250 --> 01:08:24,490
I didn't even notice the music.

1441
01:08:24,490 --> 01:08:27,730
When something sticks out a lot,

1442
01:08:27,730 --> 01:08:29,510
it can be domineering, but it wasn't.

1443
01:08:29,510 --> 01:08:31,730
But I didn't notice other things.

1444
01:08:31,730 --> 01:08:33,070
It makes you want to watch it again.

1445
01:08:33,150 --> 01:08:36,250
"What was music like? How was it shot?

1446
01:08:36,310 --> 01:08:37,800
What was the location like?"

1447
01:08:37,800 --> 01:08:38,860
It makes you watch it again.

1448
01:08:38,860 --> 01:08:41,580
This was like that. Makes you
want to watch it again.

1449
01:08:41,580 --> 01:08:43,620
I even thought I'd like to work with you.

1450
01:08:43,620 --> 01:08:45,060
Wow.

1451
01:08:45,060 --> 01:08:47,060
Which one? Director Jeong Joo?

1452
01:08:47,060 --> 01:08:49,110
But they can say no.

1453
01:08:49,110 --> 01:08:50,540
[Say it's me]

1454
01:08:50,540 --> 01:08:52,580
I learned a lot.

1455
01:08:53,520 --> 01:08:57,350
There's a scene I want to watch again.

1456
01:08:57,350 --> 01:09:01,350
After getting up from the hospital bed,
she goes, "Min Ho, don't go."

1457
01:09:01,400 --> 01:09:04,420
Min Ho, don't go.

1458
01:09:04,420 --> 01:09:07,370
This is something that could've been overlooked.

1459
01:09:07,370 --> 01:09:10,060
The script could've told her to

1460
01:09:10,060 --> 01:09:13,460
blow the tissues out and say, "Min Ho, don't go."

1461
01:09:13,460 --> 01:09:15,860
But it was "Min Ho," snort, "don't go."

1462
01:09:15,860 --> 01:09:17,280
That's a totally different thing.

1463
01:09:17,280 --> 01:09:21,880
- The rhythm.
- That's the comedic style I love.

1464
01:09:21,880 --> 01:09:24,620
I have nothing to criticize. I loved it.

1465
01:09:24,620 --> 01:09:25,640
Thank you.

1466
01:09:25,640 --> 01:09:27,340
[Rave reviews for Team "Black Out Hanami"]

1467
01:09:27,340 --> 01:09:29,950
You said I change things all the time.

1468
01:09:29,950 --> 01:09:32,650
That was ad-libbed on set, too.

1469
01:09:32,650 --> 01:09:35,730
- The tissues?
- Compared to other characters,

1470
01:09:35,730 --> 01:09:39,220
she lacked impact despite being the lead.

1471
01:09:39,220 --> 01:09:41,250
So, I told the actress to add that on set.

1472
01:09:41,250 --> 01:09:44,190
I said, "I'll put this in your nose later."

1473
01:09:44,190 --> 01:09:47,020
Do I do it after saying "Min Ho"?

1474
01:09:47,020 --> 01:09:49,260
You stay this way and...

1475
01:09:49,260 --> 01:09:52,520
Min Ho, I have a trauma from the past.

1476
01:09:52,520 --> 01:09:53,940
- I love it.
- Like that.

1477
01:09:53,940 --> 01:09:56,150
Do I say the line after blowing?

1478
01:09:56,150 --> 01:09:58,890
No, like this. Min Ho... Don't go.

1479
01:09:58,890 --> 01:10:00,400
- That's it.
- Like that?

1480
01:10:00,400 --> 01:10:02,460
Min Ho... Don't go.

1481
01:10:02,460 --> 01:10:04,360
[Satisfied]

1482
01:10:04,360 --> 01:10:06,350
Director Han, I stand corrected.

1483
01:10:06,350 --> 01:10:10,200
You're the director the actors
can't help but love.

1484
01:10:10,200 --> 01:10:12,810
You might be that kind of director.

1485
01:10:12,810 --> 01:10:15,890
- Thank you.
- From what I heard,

1486
01:10:15,890 --> 01:10:20,780
Director Jeong Joo was mostly
in charge of casting.

1487
01:10:20,780 --> 01:10:23,000
Yes, I have a box of jewels.

1488
01:10:23,000 --> 01:10:24,660
His box of jewels.

1489
01:10:24,660 --> 01:10:26,240
How did you get to know them?

1490
01:10:26,240 --> 01:10:29,240
Since I've worked on many projects,

1491
01:10:29,250 --> 01:10:32,910
I've been saving their contacts.
They're my secret weapons.

1492
01:10:32,910 --> 01:10:34,950
I think you used them well.

1493
01:10:34,950 --> 01:10:37,090
- Right.
- For directors,

1494
01:10:37,090 --> 01:10:41,110
that can be a very valuable thing.

1495
01:10:41,110 --> 01:10:43,210
[Thank you]

1496
01:10:43,210 --> 01:10:44,870
Out of the eight teams,

1497
01:10:44,870 --> 01:10:47,550
only the Top 5 teams survive in Round 2.

1498
01:10:47,550 --> 01:10:48,960
Everyone, focus.

1499
01:10:48,960 --> 01:10:53,240
Depending on the result of
Team "Black Out Girl Hanami,"

1500
01:10:53,240 --> 01:10:57,160
we'll get the first surviving team.

1501
01:10:57,160 --> 01:10:58,590
[If they rank in first place,]

1502
01:10:58,990 --> 01:11:00,590
[they will be in Top 5 and survive!]

1503
01:11:00,590 --> 01:11:02,750
Team "Black Out Girl Hanami,"

1504
01:11:02,750 --> 01:11:05,370
- are you confident you'll be in first place?
- Yes.

1505
01:11:05,370 --> 01:11:08,490
[They have the fewest number of stops so far]

1506
01:11:09,150 --> 01:11:15,350
I'm thinking we might end up in first place.

1507
01:11:17,350 --> 01:11:19,930
We got more stops than I thought.

1508
01:11:19,930 --> 01:11:22,660
I thought we might be at risk.

1509
01:11:22,660 --> 01:11:26,310
Let's reveal the result.

1510
01:11:26,310 --> 01:11:29,560
[Which team will be the first surviving team?]

1511
01:11:29,560 --> 01:11:32,000
Team "Black Out Girl Hanami."

1512
01:11:33,030 --> 01:11:37,510
Their average viewing time.

1513
01:11:37,510 --> 01:11:38,590
Please reveal it.

1514
01:11:38,590 --> 01:11:41,630
Could it be over 100 seconds?

1515
01:11:41,630 --> 01:11:43,200
If it's past 106 seconds...

1516
01:11:43,200 --> 01:11:45,950
They'll be in first place immediately.

1517
01:11:45,950 --> 01:11:48,530
They'll get to survive immediately.

1518
01:11:48,530 --> 01:11:52,470
Team "Black Out Girl Hanami." What could it be?

1519
01:11:59,750 --> 01:12:01,200
[Oh?]

1520
01:12:01,930 --> 01:12:05,250
[Average viewing time - 107.36 seconds]

1521
01:12:05,250 --> 01:12:07,930
One second difference.

1522
01:12:07,930 --> 01:12:11,200
- Wow.
- That was so close.

1523
01:12:11,200 --> 01:12:14,580
- It was less than a second.
- They went over 100 seconds.

1524
01:12:14,580 --> 01:12:16,670
Team "Black Out Girl Hanami."

1525
01:12:16,670 --> 01:12:21,000
With the average viewing time of 107.36 seconds,

1526
01:12:21,000 --> 01:12:23,030
they're in first place and survived this round.

1527
01:12:23,030 --> 01:12:25,560
- Congratulations.
- Congrats. You survive for now.

1528
01:12:25,560 --> 01:12:29,540
Wow, that'd put them in a comfortable place.

1529
01:12:29,540 --> 01:12:30,960
- Are you satisfied?
- Are you?

1530
01:12:30,960 --> 01:12:32,850
You're in first place.

1531
01:12:32,850 --> 01:12:34,670
Thank you, everyone.

1532
01:12:35,870 --> 01:12:37,490
Yes.

1533
01:12:37,490 --> 01:12:39,240
Thankfully, we survived.

1534
01:12:39,240 --> 01:12:42,250
I'm glad I have something
to say to my wife later.

1535
01:12:42,250 --> 01:12:45,230
If I got eliminated, she would've yelled at me.

1536
01:12:45,230 --> 01:12:47,210
Love you, Honey.

1537
01:12:47,210 --> 01:12:49,520
We love our crew, too.

1538
01:12:49,520 --> 01:12:52,520
You're in first place. Congratulations.

1539
01:12:52,520 --> 01:12:54,500
Short drama directing competition show.

1540
01:12:54,550 --> 01:12:57,020
Director's Arena, Round 2.

1541
01:12:57,020 --> 01:12:59,650
No. 1 short-form director
and the S company's director.

1542
01:12:59,650 --> 01:13:02,330
- He's in so many short dramas.
- The short drama prince.

1543
01:13:02,330 --> 01:13:03,510
That part was awkward.

1544
01:13:03,510 --> 01:13:04,970
I think my expectation was too high.

1545
01:13:04,970 --> 01:13:07,070
Experienced Eun Jong Hun.

1546
01:13:07,070 --> 01:13:10,360
- The fighter, Jang Yu Jin.
- A battle of masters.

1547
01:13:10,360 --> 01:13:12,610
They'll compare him to Director Lee Joon Ik.

1548
01:13:12,610 --> 01:13:14,080
That's a lot of pressure.

1549
01:13:14,080 --> 01:13:16,110
- I'll say it confidently.
- I'm confident.

1550
01:13:16,110 --> 01:13:17,250
The lady and her servant?

1551
01:13:17,250 --> 01:13:19,480
I wonder if Director Yang would be happy.

1552
01:13:19,480 --> 01:13:20,620
[Even a water truck is here]

1553
01:13:20,620 --> 01:13:22,150
[A legendary scale]

1554
01:13:22,150 --> 01:13:25,620
First-place director, Lee Yoo Jin,
and third-place director, Han Soo Ji.

1555
01:13:25,620 --> 01:13:28,100
- They're finalists.
- Those two teamed up?

1556
01:13:28,100 --> 01:13:29,630
I think we'll lose, to be honest.

1557
01:13:29,630 --> 01:13:31,530
I think we'll be in first place.

1558
01:13:31,550 --> 01:13:35,150
[Can they beat the first-place team?]

1559
01:13:35,150 --> 01:13:36,030
[And]

1560
01:13:36,030 --> 01:13:37,420
Round 3 mission.

1561
01:13:37,420 --> 01:13:38,610
[1:1 Death Match]

1562
01:13:38,610 --> 01:13:39,710
Death match?

1563
01:13:39,710 --> 01:13:42,520
- What's wrong with them?
- I panicked.

1564
01:13:42,520 --> 01:13:43,960
It's too much.

1565
01:13:43,960 --> 01:13:45,760
The broadcasting industry is full of jerks.

1566
01:13:45,760 --> 01:13:47,790
[The battle for survival begins now!]
